1
00:00:57,250 --> 00:01:02,400
{y:i}<font face="Tw Cen MT Condensed">{\an2}SubText: NoRMITA.326</font>

2
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:48,299
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The next stop is Broad Street.
Broad Street will be next.</font></b>

3
00:04:59,255 --> 00:05:01,739
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Upstairs. This way.</font></b>

4
00:05:10,032 --> 00:05:13,455
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">He didn't come up this way? Anything?</font></b>

5
00:05:15,871 --> 00:05:18,222
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Excuse me.
- Excuse me.</font></b>

6
00:05:36,325 --> 00:05:38,626
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Go ahead and park around the corner.</font></b>

7
00:08:51,186 --> 00:08:53,022
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Visitors.</font></b>

8
00:08:53,222 --> 00:08:57,608
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Do you mind if I fetch my teeth?
- Colonel, would you turn around, please?</font></b>

9
00:09:00,262 --> 00:09:03,214
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Sit down on the bed.
- Let's go.</font></b>

10
00:09:11,273 --> 00:09:13,843
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">They're in the...the teeth
are in the...on the sink.</font></b>

11
00:09:13,943 --> 00:09:18,047
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Look at me. We are agents from the
Federal Bureau of Investigation.</font></b>

12
00:09:18,147 --> 00:09:20,850
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Look at me! I'm talking to you.</font></b>

13
00:09:20,950 --> 00:09:24,987
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We've received information concerning
your involvement in espionage.</font></b>

14
00:09:25,087 --> 00:09:28,357
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You can either cooperate with us right now,
or you'll be under arrest.</font></b>

15
00:09:28,457 --> 00:09:31,294
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Do you understand, Colonel?
- No, not really.</font></b>

16
00:09:31,394 --> 00:09:34,830
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Why do you keep calling me "Colonel"?</font></b>

17
00:09:34,930 --> 00:09:38,901
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- You need to get dressed.
- We have to search your apartment.</font></b>

18
00:09:39,001 --> 00:09:42,705
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Would you mind if I...cleaned my palette?</font></b>

19
00:09:42,805 --> 00:09:45,541
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The paints, it'll get ruined otherwise.</font></b>

20
00:09:45,641 --> 00:09:48,025
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It's just behind you there.</font></b>

21
00:09:49,078 --> 00:09:52,081
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I have a cloth myself. Thank you.</font></b>

22
00:09:52,381 --> 00:09:54,850
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Alright, start searching the place.
- Thank you.</font></b>

23
00:09:54,950 --> 00:09:57,186
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Alright, search the mattress,
the bed, the floorboards...</font></b>

24
00:09:57,286 --> 00:10:01,299
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Would you put that in the ashtray
on the window sill there?</font></b>

25
00:10:01,299 --> 00:10:02,072
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Take a good look at that desk.</font></b>

26
00:10:04,927 --> 00:10:07,211
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Let's see the desk.</font></b>

27
00:10:13,335 --> 00:10:15,753
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Wouldn't want to get this ruined.</font></b>

28
00:10:29,184 --> 00:10:31,454
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Don't say "my guy".</font></b>

29
00:10:31,554 --> 00:10:34,190
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">He's not "my guy".</font></b>

30
00:10:34,290 --> 00:10:37,460
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yes, he's "your guy". Who
are we talking about?</font></b>

31
00:10:37,560 --> 00:10:41,630
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We're talking about a guy who
was insured by my client.</font></b>

32
00:10:41,730 --> 00:10:44,248
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So, don't make him "my guy".</font></b>

33
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:46,368
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Okay, fine.</font></b>

34
00:10:46,468 --> 00:10:49,472
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">My point is, the guy insured by your client,</font></b>

35
00:10:49,572 --> 00:10:52,475
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">he doesn't deny that any of
these things happened.</font></b>

36
00:10:52,575 --> 00:10:55,144
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">"These...these things"?</font></b>

37
00:10:55,244 --> 00:10:57,513
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yes, these five things.</font></b>

38
00:10:57,613 --> 00:11:01,016
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Wait, hold it, hold it, hold it.
Not five things.</font></b>

39
00:11:01,116 --> 00:11:04,053
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- One thing.
- Clearly, it's five things.</font></b>

40
00:11:04,153 --> 00:11:08,357
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, I'm sorry, it's not clear to me.
Five things? Explain it to me.</font></b>

41
00:11:08,457 --> 00:11:11,627
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- It's self-evident.
- Okay, then tell me what happened.</font></b>

42
00:11:11,727 --> 00:11:15,177
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Tell me the story in a way that
makes sense for five things.</font></b>

43
00:11:15,277 --> 00:11:18,801
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Fine, absolutely. Your guy is...
- Not my guy. Insured by my client.</font></b>

44
00:11:18,901 --> 00:11:22,071
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The guy insured by your client is
driving down State Highway 19</font></b>

45
00:11:22,171 --> 00:11:24,607
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">when he loses control of his car
and hits my five guys,</font></b>

46
00:11:24,707 --> 00:11:28,310
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">the five guys who hired me to represent them
because you're not honoring your claim.</font></b>

47
00:11:28,410 --> 00:11:32,047
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You mean my client is not honoring
the claim, the insurance company?</font></b>

48
00:11:32,147 --> 00:11:34,817
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Mr. Donovan, we're all clear
on who's who, here.</font></b>

49
00:11:34,917 --> 00:11:38,687
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Except my client honors every claim.
They do, Mr. Bates.</font></b>

50
00:11:38,787 --> 00:11:41,824
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Every single legitimate claim, up
to the limit of their liability,</font></b>

51
00:11:41,924 --> 00:11:46,161
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">which is $100,000 per accident,
in the case of this man's policy.</font></b>

52
00:11:46,261 --> 00:11:51,100
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And this is one claim. According to your
description, "he hit my five guys".</font></b>

53
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:54,136
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The guy insured by my client
had one accident.</font></b>

54
00:11:54,236 --> 00:11:58,624
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">One, one, one. Losing control of the car
and hitting five motorcyclists.</font></b>

55
00:11:58,724 --> 00:12:02,244
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">From their point of view,
five things happened.</font></b>

56
00:12:02,344 --> 00:12:05,896
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, look, Bob. May I? Bob?</font></b>

57
00:12:06,148 --> 00:12:08,083
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">"Jim."</font></b>

58
00:12:08,183 --> 00:12:12,087
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">If I go bowling and I throw a strike, one thing
happened. Ten things didn't happen.</font></b>

59
00:12:12,187 --> 00:12:15,871
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Jim, my guys aren't bowling pins, as much as
your guy may have treated them as such.</font></b>

60
00:12:15,971 --> 00:12:20,162
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">If...let me finish. Let me finish. If your
house is insured for $100,000</font></b>

61
00:12:20,262 --> 00:12:23,599
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">and a tornado carries it away,
it carried away one house.</font></b>

62
00:12:23,699 --> 00:12:27,870
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It didn't pick up every stick of furniture
and destroy it in a separate incident.</font></b>

63
00:12:27,970 --> 00:12:30,639
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">If that is what you're saying...</font></b>

64
00:12:30,739 --> 00:12:34,009
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">well, then there is never
any limit to our liability</font></b>

65
00:12:34,109 --> 00:12:37,046
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">and that is the end of the
insurance business.</font></b>

66
00:12:37,146 --> 00:12:40,323
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And then, Bob, nobody is safe.</font></b>

67
00:12:44,820 --> 00:12:47,156
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Watters, Cowan and Donovan.
How may I direct your call?</font></b>

68
00:12:47,256 --> 00:12:49,959
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Morning, Mr. Donovan.
- Good morning, Alison.</font></b>

69
00:12:50,059 --> 00:12:52,127
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I moved your 9:00 a.m. with Prudential, sir.</font></b>

70
00:12:52,227 --> 00:12:54,979
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Why did you do that?
- I asked her to.</font></b>

71
00:12:55,498 --> 00:12:56,832
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Is everything alright, Tom?</font></b>

72
00:12:56,932 --> 00:12:59,951
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Why don't you leave your stuff with Alison.
Come on inside.</font></b>

73
00:13:00,770 --> 00:13:04,139
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Something pretty important has come up.
Somebody's here to see us.</font></b>

74
00:13:04,239 --> 00:13:08,511
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Natalie's getting your coffee. Nescafe,
cream, two lumps, right?</font></b>

75
00:13:08,611 --> 00:13:11,128
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">That's right. Thanks.</font></b>

76
00:13:12,147 --> 00:13:13,282
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Lynn!
- Jim!</font></b>

77
00:13:13,382 --> 00:13:16,719
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Nice to see you again. How's the family?
- Great, good. Thanks. How's Annie?</font></b>

78
00:13:16,819 --> 00:13:19,188
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Homicidal. We had the in-laws
for the holiday.</font></b>

79
00:13:19,288 --> 00:13:22,424
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, if she acts on it, she'll
have good representation.</font></b>

80
00:13:22,524 --> 00:13:24,908
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Now, what's up?</font></b>

81
00:13:30,299 --> 00:13:35,271
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Okay, here's the thing. The Soviet spy they caught,
we want you to defend him.</font></b>

82
00:13:35,371 --> 00:13:37,888
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Here's the indictment.</font></b>

83
00:13:43,212 --> 00:13:46,982
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- I'm not sure I wanna pick that up.
- The accused doesn't know any lawyers.</font></b>

84
00:13:47,082 --> 00:13:50,319
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The federal court tossed it into our lap.</font></b>

85
00:13:50,419 --> 00:13:54,023
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The Bar Committee took a vote.
You're the unanimous choice.</font></b>

86
00:13:54,123 --> 00:13:56,892
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It was important to us...it's important
to our country, Jim,</font></b>

87
00:13:56,992 --> 00:13:59,061
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">that this man is seen as
getting a fair shake.</font></b>

88
00:13:59,161 --> 00:14:01,096
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">American justice will be on trial.</font></b>

89
00:14:01,196 --> 00:14:04,016
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, of course, when you put it that way,
it's an honor to be asked.</font></b>

90
00:14:04,116 --> 00:14:08,737
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But...Lynn, I'm an insurance lawyer. I
haven't done criminal work in years.</font></b>

91
00:14:08,837 --> 00:14:13,025
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It's like riding a bike, isn't it? You distinguished
yourself at Nuremberg.</font></b>

92
00:14:13,125 --> 00:14:15,778
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- I was on the prosecution team.
- Not the point.</font></b>

93
00:14:15,878 --> 00:14:18,162
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You're no stranger to criminal law.</font></b>

94
00:14:18,262 --> 00:14:22,087
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Jim, look at the situation. The man
is publicly reviled.</font></b>

95
00:14:22,187 --> 00:14:25,020
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- And I will be, too.
- Yes, in more ignorant quarters.</font></b>

96
00:14:25,120 --> 00:14:28,891
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But that's exactly why this has to be done,
and capably done.</font></b>

97
00:14:28,991 --> 00:14:34,010
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It can't look like our justice system
tosses people on the ash heap.</font></b>

98
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:40,918
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Suppose I did, what's
the evidence look like?</font></b>

99
00:14:41,436 --> 00:14:42,938
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Pretty overwhelming.</font></b>

100
00:14:43,438 --> 00:14:45,574
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Great. Great.</font></b>

101
00:14:45,674 --> 00:14:49,122
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Everyone will hate me
but at least I'll lose.</font></b>

102
00:14:50,279 --> 00:14:54,783
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, what do you think, Tom? The firm will suffer.
I have work here.</font></b>

103
00:14:54,883 --> 00:14:58,954
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I think it's a patriotic duty.
It's an important mission.</font></b>

104
00:14:59,054 --> 00:15:00,790
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I told Lynn, the firm can't say no,</font></b>

105
00:15:00,890 --> 00:15:04,307
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">and you'd have a tough time
saying no, too.</font></b>

106
00:15:04,910 --> 00:15:07,613
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I think you have to defend
the son of a bitch.</font></b>

107
00:15:07,763 --> 00:15:11,166
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- So, you're doing it?
- Doing what?</font></b>

108
00:15:11,266 --> 00:15:14,303
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Defending Abel, the Soviet spy.</font></b>

109
00:15:14,403 --> 00:15:15,637
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I may. I have to speak to...</font></b>

110
00:15:15,737 --> 00:15:18,307
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Wait, how do you know? Did they post it
on the bulletin board?</font></b>

111
00:15:18,407 --> 00:15:24,000
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- No, I was talking to Richard Earl...
- If I do this, I'm going to need your help.</font></b>

112
00:15:25,781 --> 00:15:28,014
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Can you work tonight?</font></b>

113
00:15:28,784 --> 00:15:31,283
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, I have a dinner date, sir.</font></b>

114
00:15:33,823 --> 00:15:37,657
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It's Tuesday, right? Yeah, no, I'm free,
completely free. Thank you, sir.</font></b>

115
00:15:41,396 --> 00:15:42,965
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But it's also an honor.</font></b>

116
00:15:43,065 --> 00:15:45,100
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And the Bar Association asked me</font></b>

117
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:48,604
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">because they want to show that even
a spy gets a capable advocate.</font></b>

118
00:15:48,704 --> 00:15:50,873
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, maybe it's the kind of honor
we could do without.</font></b>

119
00:15:50,973 --> 00:15:53,576
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Hey, honey, what are you doing home?</font></b>

120
00:15:53,676 --> 00:15:58,413
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- I got stood up.
- Well, that's despicable.</font></b>

121
00:15:58,513 --> 00:16:01,116
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Who is this knot-head?
- I'd rather not say.</font></b>

122
00:16:01,216 --> 00:16:04,286
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, sit down. We just started.
People are scared.</font></b>

123
00:16:04,386 --> 00:16:08,691
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">They're building bomb shelters to protect
themselves from people like this man.</font></b>

124
00:16:08,791 --> 00:16:13,428
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I go to the store, people are buying
canned food and potassium tablets.</font></b>

125
00:16:13,528 --> 00:16:16,265
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It's all about this man and
what he represents.</font></b>

126
00:16:16,365 --> 00:16:18,778
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- He's a threat to all of us. A traitor.
- Who's a traitor?</font></b>

127
00:16:18,878 --> 00:16:21,136
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- The Rosenbergs were traitors.
- Who were they?</font></b>

128
00:16:21,236 --> 00:16:23,038
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">They gave atomic secrets to the Russians.</font></b>

129
00:16:23,138 --> 00:16:25,140
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">They were Americans. They
betrayed their country.</font></b>

130
00:16:25,240 --> 00:16:28,511
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You can't accuse Abel of being a traitor.
He's not an American.</font></b>

131
00:16:28,811 --> 00:16:31,680
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Oh, listen to yourself. You're
defending him already.</font></b>

132
00:16:31,780 --> 00:16:34,783
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You're rehearsing it on me. You said you
were just thinking about taking it.</font></b>

133
00:16:34,883 --> 00:16:37,786
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I am just thinking about it,
just very hard.</font></b>

134
00:16:37,886 --> 00:16:40,656
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Everyone deserves a defense.
Every person matters.</font></b>

135
00:16:40,756 --> 00:16:43,959
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Jim, what do we deserve? Do you know
how people will look at us?</font></b>

136
00:16:44,059 --> 00:16:46,461
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The family of a man trying to free a traitor?</font></b>

137
00:16:46,561 --> 00:16:49,553
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- He's not a traitor, Mary.
- Yes. Roger, get that! He's not a traitor...</font></b>

138
00:16:49,653 --> 00:16:52,268
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Why do I have to do all the work?
- You wait till we say grace.</font></b>

139
00:16:52,368 --> 00:16:56,004
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">He's the most unpopular man in this country,
and you're trying to take second place!</font></b>

140
00:16:56,104 --> 00:16:59,411
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Yeah, and I'm third.
- Carol, you just dated the wrong guy.</font></b>

141
00:16:59,511 --> 00:17:02,244
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Mary, don't make this an argument when
we're not having an argument.</font></b>

142
00:17:02,344 --> 00:17:06,025
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You're against him, I'm for him? I'm not for him.
I'm not for the Russians spying on us.</font></b>

143
00:17:06,125 --> 00:17:09,184
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'm for his right to have a defense
in a court of law,</font></b>

144
00:17:09,284 --> 00:17:12,522
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- which is why they call it a court of law.
- I didn't mean to interrupt dinner.</font></b>

145
00:17:12,622 --> 00:17:16,781
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- A court of law...hey, Doug.
- Oh, no, not at all. Hello, Doug.</font></b>

146
00:17:16,881 --> 00:17:20,002
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Jim was just flailing.
- A kangaroo court. I'm not flailing.</font></b>

147
00:17:20,102 --> 00:17:23,930
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Go ahead, Doug, you can join us for dinner.
We're having meatloaf tonight.</font></b>

148
00:17:25,600 --> 00:17:29,304
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So, you came over to help Jim think about
whether he's taking the case?</font></b>

149
00:17:29,404 --> 00:17:33,372
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Oh, we're taking it! It's exciting, isn't it?</font></b>

150
00:17:40,382 --> 00:17:43,485
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Lord, we thank thee for thy blessings
we are about to receive.</font></b>

151
00:17:43,585 --> 00:17:46,125
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Thy bounty through Christ, our Lord. Amen.</font></b>

152
00:17:53,662 --> 00:17:55,797
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Good morning, sir. My name is Jim Donovan.</font></b>

153
00:17:55,897 --> 00:17:59,768
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">These are my credentials. I am a partner
in Watters, Cowan and Donovan.</font></b>

154
00:17:59,868 --> 00:18:04,136
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I was admitted to the New York Bar in 1941.</font></b>

155
00:18:07,376 --> 00:18:11,280
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You have been charged with three counts
and 19 overt acts.</font></b>

156
00:18:11,380 --> 00:18:15,817
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Conspiracy to transmit United States defense
and atomic secrets to the Soviet Union,</font></b>

157
00:18:15,917 --> 00:18:20,419
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">conspiracy to gather secrets, and failing
to register as a foreign agent.</font></b>

158
00:18:25,494 --> 00:18:28,560
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Do many foreign agents register?</font></b>

159
00:18:32,701 --> 00:18:36,171
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">If you don't mind my asking, sir...</font></b>

160
00:18:36,271 --> 00:18:40,506
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">since your arrest, where have you been?</font></b>

161
00:18:42,845 --> 00:18:45,477
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I couldn't say for certain.</font></b>

162
00:18:46,748 --> 00:18:48,780
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You don't know?</font></b>

163
00:18:49,451 --> 00:18:54,386
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">They drove me to an airport and put me
on a plane, took me off the plane.</font></b>

164
00:18:55,624 --> 00:18:57,957
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Somewhere hot.</font></b>

165
00:18:58,560 --> 00:19:01,897
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- It's hot here.
- Hotter, very humid.</font></b>

166
00:19:02,497 --> 00:19:05,230
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">They put me in a room.</font></b>

167
00:19:06,268 --> 00:19:07,833
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Were you beaten?</font></b>

168
00:19:08,403 --> 00:19:11,640
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No. I was talked to.</font></b>

169
00:19:11,740 --> 00:19:14,743
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Offers were made.
- What do you mean?</font></b>

170
00:19:14,843 --> 00:19:19,344
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Offers of employment, to work
for your government.</font></b>

171
00:19:20,649 --> 00:19:23,018
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I was told if I cooperated,</font></b>

172
00:19:23,118 --> 00:19:26,320
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">no further charges would
be made against me.</font></b>

173
00:19:26,888 --> 00:19:29,421
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And I would be given money.</font></b>

174
00:19:30,992 --> 00:19:33,158
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And you declined?</font></b>

175
00:19:33,962 --> 00:19:35,264
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">As you see.</font></b>

176
00:19:35,964 --> 00:19:38,567
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, of course I can't endorse that.</font></b>

177
00:19:38,667 --> 00:19:42,671
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I feel duty-bound to urge you to cooperate
with the U.S. government.</font></b>

178
00:19:42,771 --> 00:19:46,842
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, I said no. Perhaps you could relay to
your friends at the CIA that I meant it.</font></b>

179
00:19:46,942 --> 00:19:49,378
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No, no, no. I...</font></b>

180
00:19:49,478 --> 00:19:52,211
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I don't work for the agency.</font></b>

181
00:19:53,115 --> 00:19:55,317
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I don't work for the government.</font></b>

182
00:19:55,417 --> 00:19:58,487
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I am here to offer my services
as your legal counsel.</font></b>

183
00:19:58,587 --> 00:20:02,362
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">If you accept them as such...</font></b>

184
00:20:02,791 --> 00:20:04,326
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I work for you.</font></b>

185
00:20:05,026 --> 00:20:07,361
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">If I accept you?</font></b>

186
00:20:13,401 --> 00:20:15,368
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Are you good at what you do?</font></b>

187
00:20:16,838 --> 00:20:19,405
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah. Yeah, I'm pretty good.</font></b>

188
00:20:21,943 --> 00:20:25,690
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Have you represented many accused spies?</font></b>

189
00:20:28,350 --> 00:20:30,911
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No, not yet.</font></b>

190
00:20:31,686 --> 00:20:34,244
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">This will be a first for the both of us.</font></b>

191
00:20:38,159 --> 00:20:39,286
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yes.</font></b>

192
00:20:41,563 --> 00:20:45,997
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Alright.
- "Alright"? You accept?</font></b>

193
00:20:47,435 --> 00:20:51,239
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Yes, alright.
- Good, okay.</font></b>

194
00:20:51,339 --> 00:20:55,800
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Let's start here. If you are firm in your resolve
not to cooperate with the U.S. government...</font></b>

195
00:20:55,900 --> 00:20:56,344
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I am.</font></b>

196
00:20:56,444 --> 00:21:01,183
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah. Then do not talk to anybody else about
your case, inside of government or out.</font></b>

197
00:21:01,283 --> 00:21:04,419
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Except to me, to the extent
that you trust me.</font></b>

198
00:21:04,519 --> 00:21:06,455
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I have a mandate to serve you.
Nobody else does.</font></b>

199
00:21:06,555 --> 00:21:10,492
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Quite frankly, everybody else has an interest
in sending you to the electric chair.</font></b>

200
00:21:10,592 --> 00:21:12,558
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Alright.</font></b>

201
00:21:15,163 --> 00:21:17,833
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You don't seem alarmed.</font></b>

202
00:21:22,103 --> 00:21:23,736
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Would it help?</font></b>

203
00:21:33,682 --> 00:21:37,786
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I...I would like materials to draw with.</font></b>

204
00:21:37,886 --> 00:21:40,188
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">That's not possible.</font></b>

205
00:21:40,288 --> 00:21:44,156
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">A pencil, a piece of paper. Cigarettes.</font></b>

206
00:21:46,194 --> 00:21:47,727
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Please?</font></b>

207
00:21:55,036 --> 00:22:00,775
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Mr. Donovan, you have men like me
doing the same for your country.</font></b>

208
00:22:01,543 --> 00:22:03,745
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">If they were caught,</font></b>

209
00:22:03,845 --> 00:22:07,846
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'm sure that you would wish them
to be treated well.</font></b>

210
00:22:11,319 --> 00:22:14,254
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- What's your name?
- Francis Gary Powers.</font></b>

211
00:22:16,558 --> 00:22:18,126
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Rank, service?</font></b>

212
00:22:18,226 --> 00:22:21,427
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">First Lieutenant, United States Air Force.</font></b>

213
00:22:22,697 --> 00:22:26,468
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Do you have any association with the Soviet Union,
Lieutenant Powers?</font></b>

214
00:22:26,568 --> 00:22:28,803
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Kidding?
- Just answer the questions, Lieutenant.</font></b>

215
00:22:28,903 --> 00:22:31,206
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yes, no, or as simply as you can.</font></b>

216
00:22:31,306 --> 00:22:33,608
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Do you have any association
with the Soviet Union?</font></b>

217
00:22:33,708 --> 00:22:35,486
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Hell, no.</font></b>

218
00:22:37,078 --> 00:22:39,511
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Do you know why you're here?</font></b>

219
00:22:40,548 --> 00:22:42,451
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Is that a no?</font></b>

220
00:22:42,651 --> 00:22:45,086
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yes. I mean...</font></b>

221
00:22:45,186 --> 00:22:49,157
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No, it's just "no". Yes, I have absolutely
no idea why I'm here.</font></b>

222
00:22:49,257 --> 00:22:51,991
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Eyes front, Lieutenant.
- Yes, sir.</font></b>

223
00:23:09,444 --> 00:23:11,877
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">How'd you do in there, Gary?</font></b>

224
00:23:12,414 --> 00:23:15,250
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Pretty good. Think I got my name right.</font></b>

225
00:23:16,250 --> 00:23:19,284
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You probably outscored Shinn, then.</font></b>

226
00:23:20,254 --> 00:23:22,491
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Who's winning?
- That would be me.</font></b>

227
00:23:22,591 --> 00:23:24,259
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Oh. Well, deal me in.</font></b>

228
00:23:24,359 --> 00:23:26,695
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So, these are all mine, then.</font></b>

229
00:23:26,795 --> 00:23:29,237
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I told you boys not to play with him.</font></b>

230
00:23:55,757 --> 00:23:58,590
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Okay, drivers, here's the deal.</font></b>

231
00:23:59,260 --> 00:24:03,210
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You've been selected for a mission which
you are not to discuss with anyone</font></b>

232
00:24:03,310 --> 00:24:06,301
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">outside of this room. No one.</font></b>

233
00:24:06,401 --> 00:24:08,670
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I don't care who you trust.</font></b>

234
00:24:08,770 --> 00:24:12,374
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Wife, mother, sweetheart. The good Lord
when you pray at night.</font></b>

235
00:24:12,474 --> 00:24:16,901
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You don't tell any of them anything
of what I'm about to tell you.</font></b>

236
00:24:18,847 --> 00:24:22,350
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Each of you drivers has met
certain qualifications.</font></b>

237
00:24:22,450 --> 00:24:24,586
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">High level security clearance.</font></b>

238
00:24:24,686 --> 00:24:28,222
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Exceptional pilot ratings in excess
of the required hours flight time</font></b>

239
00:24:28,322 --> 00:24:30,308
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">in a single-seat aircraft.</font></b>

240
00:24:30,408 --> 00:24:33,261
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We are engaged in a war.</font></b>

241
00:24:33,361 --> 00:24:37,392
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">This war does not, for the moment, involve
men-at-arms. It involves information.</font></b>

242
00:24:37,592 --> 00:24:39,618
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You will be collecting information.</font></b>

243
00:24:39,768 --> 00:24:42,437
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You will be gathering intelligence
about the enemy.</font></b>

244
00:24:42,537 --> 00:24:46,008
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The intelligence you gather could
give us the upper hand</font></b>

245
00:24:46,108 --> 00:24:50,141
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">in a full thermonuclear exchange
with the Soviet Union.</font></b>

246
00:24:51,179 --> 00:24:53,512
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Or it could prevent one.</font></b>

247
00:24:53,848 --> 00:24:57,786
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">For public purposes, as far
as your wife or mother</font></b>

248
00:24:57,886 --> 00:25:01,623
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">or sweetheart or the good Lord above,
your mission does not exist.</font></b>

249
00:25:01,723 --> 00:25:04,593
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">If it does not exist, you do not exist.</font></b>

250
00:25:04,693 --> 00:25:08,094
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You cannot be shot down.
You cannot be captured.</font></b>

251
00:25:14,536 --> 00:25:17,168
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You work for the CIA now.</font></b>

252
00:25:28,683 --> 00:25:33,318
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So, Jim, I heard your guy is speaking
with a phony accent.</font></b>

253
00:25:33,722 --> 00:25:35,557
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Does he keep that up all the time?</font></b>

254
00:25:35,657 --> 00:25:38,226
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Actually, I'm pretty sure that's
just the way he talks.</font></b>

255
00:25:38,326 --> 00:25:40,662
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">He's got the Russian name
but a British passport.</font></b>

256
00:25:40,762 --> 00:25:43,398
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, I doubt that that's genuine.</font></b>

257
00:25:43,498 --> 00:25:46,200
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So, Jim, where are we?
I see here...</font></b>

258
00:25:46,300 --> 00:25:48,236
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yes...Judge, you see,</font></b>

259
00:25:48,336 --> 00:25:52,741
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I just don't think that three weeks
is going to do it, here.</font></b>

260
00:25:52,841 --> 00:25:54,943
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We...got a massive amount
of evidence, as you know.</font></b>

261
00:25:55,043 --> 00:25:57,345
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- You wanna postpone?
- Six weeks.</font></b>

262
00:25:57,445 --> 00:26:00,649
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I mean, there's just myself and
my associate, basically.</font></b>

263
00:26:00,749 --> 00:26:03,382
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Jim, is this serious?
- Sir?</font></b>

264
00:26:06,154 --> 00:26:07,656
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Is this serious?</font></b>

265
00:26:07,856 --> 00:26:11,059
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yes. Yes, indeed, it is. You
can see in the filing...</font></b>

266
00:26:11,159 --> 00:26:13,738
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Jim, this man is a Soviet spy.</font></b>

267
00:26:13,838 --> 00:26:16,575
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Allegedly.
- Come on, Counselor!</font></b>

268
00:26:18,266 --> 00:26:19,601
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Your Honor.</font></b>

269
00:26:19,701 --> 00:26:23,405
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Of course, I salute you. We all salute you
for taking on a thankless task.</font></b>

270
00:26:23,505 --> 00:26:27,876
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">This man has to have due process.
But let's not kid each other.</font></b>

271
00:26:27,976 --> 00:26:30,745
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">He'll receive a capable defense.</font></b>

272
00:26:30,845 --> 00:26:34,382
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And, God willing, he'll be convicted.</font></b>

273
00:26:34,482 --> 00:26:37,452
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Come on, Counselor. Let's
not play games with this.</font></b>

274
00:26:37,552 --> 00:26:39,687
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Not in my courtroom.</font></b>

275
00:26:39,787 --> 00:26:41,623
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We have a date...</font></b>

276
00:26:41,823 --> 00:26:44,556
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">and we're going to trial.</font></b>

277
00:26:52,834 --> 00:26:54,536
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Taxi!</font></b>

278
00:26:54,836 --> 00:26:58,228
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Taxi! I see your light on!</font></b>

279
00:26:58,328 --> 00:27:00,675
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Son of a bitch.</font></b>

280
00:27:00,775 --> 00:27:03,411
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Can't wait to get back to Manhattan.</font></b>

281
00:27:03,511 --> 00:27:06,033
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">His light was on, right?</font></b>

282
00:27:06,133 --> 00:27:07,980
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Son of a bitch.</font></b>

283
00:27:54,696 --> 00:27:57,765
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Against their level of comfort.
The statute hasn't changed.</font></b>

284
00:27:57,865 --> 00:27:59,400
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Oh, excuse me, sir.</font></b>

285
00:27:59,500 --> 00:28:01,767
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Pardon me. Sorry.</font></b>

286
00:28:32,400 --> 00:28:34,266
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Mr. Donovan.</font></b>

287
00:28:36,704 --> 00:28:38,170
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">What?</font></b>

288
00:28:41,609 --> 00:28:42,931
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">What?</font></b>

289
00:28:55,323 --> 00:28:57,125
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">CIA.</font></b>

290
00:28:57,225 --> 00:28:59,024
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah.</font></b>

291
00:28:59,127 --> 00:29:01,392
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I just wanted to chat.</font></b>

292
00:29:04,566 --> 00:29:09,101
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- How's the case going?
- Case is going great. Couldn't be better.</font></b>

293
00:29:10,905 --> 00:29:13,238
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Has your guy talked?</font></b>

294
00:29:16,677 --> 00:29:18,247
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Excuse me.</font></b>

295
00:29:18,847 --> 00:29:22,381
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You met him. Has he talked?
Has he said anything yet?</font></b>

296
00:29:23,952 --> 00:29:27,756
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- We're not having this conversation.
- No, of course not.</font></b>

297
00:29:27,856 --> 00:29:30,058
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No, I mean, we really are not having it.</font></b>

298
00:29:30,158 --> 00:29:33,795
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You're asking me to violate
attorney-client privilege.</font></b>

299
00:29:33,895 --> 00:29:35,196
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Oh, come on, Counselor.</font></b>

300
00:29:35,296 --> 00:29:37,598
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I wish people like you would quit saying
"Oh, come on, Counselor".</font></b>

301
00:29:37,698 --> 00:29:40,935
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I didn't like it the first time it happened today.
A judge said it to me twice.</font></b>

302
00:29:41,035 --> 00:29:44,371
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And the more I hear it,
the more I don't like it.</font></b>

303
00:29:46,307 --> 00:29:48,843
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Okay, well, listen, I understand
attorney-client privilege.</font></b>

304
00:29:48,943 --> 00:29:51,980
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I understand all the legal gamesmanship.</font></b>

305
00:29:52,080 --> 00:29:54,716
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And I understand that's
how you make a living.</font></b>

306
00:29:54,816 --> 00:29:58,683
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But I'm talking to you about
something else.</font></b>

307
00:29:59,587 --> 00:30:01,723
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The security of your country.</font></b>

308
00:30:01,823 --> 00:30:04,893
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And I'm sorry if the way
I put it offends you.</font></b>

309
00:30:04,993 --> 00:30:08,596
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But we need to know what
Abel is telling you.</font></b>

310
00:30:08,696 --> 00:30:10,898
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You understand me, Donovan?</font></b>

311
00:30:10,998 --> 00:30:15,634
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We need to know. Don't go "Boy Scout" on me.</font></b>

312
00:30:16,304 --> 00:30:18,090
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We don't have a rule book, here.</font></b>

313
00:30:19,307 --> 00:30:21,642
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You're Agent Hoffman, yeah?</font></b>

314
00:30:21,742 --> 00:30:23,444
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah.</font></b>

315
00:30:23,544 --> 00:30:26,614
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- German extraction.
- Yeah, so?</font></b>

316
00:30:26,714 --> 00:30:31,185
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">My name's Donovan. Irish. Both sides,
mother and father.</font></b>

317
00:30:31,285 --> 00:30:34,455
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'm Irish, you're German.</font></b>

318
00:30:34,555 --> 00:30:37,325
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But what makes us both Americans?</font></b>

319
00:30:37,425 --> 00:30:39,627
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Just one thing.</font></b>

320
00:30:39,727 --> 00:30:42,196
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">One, one, one.</font></b>

321
00:30:42,296 --> 00:30:44,332
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The rule book.</font></b>

322
00:30:44,432 --> 00:30:47,936
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We call it the Constitution and
we agree to the rules,</font></b>

323
00:30:48,036 --> 00:30:50,805
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">and that's what makes us Americans.
It's all that makes us Americans</font></b>

324
00:30:50,905 --> 00:30:54,956
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">so don't tell me there's no rule book, and
don't nod at me, you son of a bitch.</font></b>

325
00:31:05,753 --> 00:31:08,402
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Do we need to worry about you?</font></b>

326
00:31:08,890 --> 00:31:12,773
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Not if I'm left alone to do my job.</font></b>

327
00:31:26,508 --> 00:31:30,645
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">From this moment forward you will not refer
to the U-2 as a spy plane</font></b>

328
00:31:30,745 --> 00:31:32,780
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">or reconnaissance aircraft.</font></b>

329
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:34,949
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You will refer to it as "The Article".</font></b>

330
00:31:35,049 --> 00:31:38,219
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The Article has an 80-foot wingspan.</font></b>

331
00:31:38,319 --> 00:31:43,858
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Powered by a single Pratt and Whitney
J57 P-37 engine.</font></b>

332
00:31:43,958 --> 00:31:46,160
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">10,000 pounds of thrust</font></b>

333
00:31:46,260 --> 00:31:50,271
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">and a maximum speed of 430 miles an hour.</font></b>

334
00:31:50,371 --> 00:31:57,036
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">She may not be quick, but at your cruising altitude
of 70,000 feet, nothing will come close to you.</font></b>

335
00:31:57,136 --> 00:31:57,939
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">70,000?</font></b>

336
00:31:58,039 --> 00:32:00,942
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The idea is the enemy doesn't
even know you're there.</font></b>

337
00:32:01,042 --> 00:32:03,007
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It looks kind of flimsy.</font></b>

338
00:32:05,843 --> 00:32:09,810
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Every extra pound of weight costs
a foot in altitude, and...</font></b>

339
00:32:09,910 --> 00:32:12,462
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">we need to accommodate the cameras.</font></b>

340
00:32:13,721 --> 00:32:17,725
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">That's a 4,500-millimeter lens, times three.</font></b>

341
00:32:17,825 --> 00:32:19,861
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">A pin-sharp panoramic camera</font></b>

342
00:32:19,961 --> 00:32:24,732
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">four times as powerful as any aerial reconnaissance
cameras we've ever used.</font></b>

343
00:32:24,832 --> 00:32:28,169
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You're gonna be taking pictures,
lots of pictures.</font></b>

344
00:32:28,269 --> 00:32:34,642
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">At 70,000 feet, The Article can photograph
2,000 square miles of territory in one pass.</font></b>

345
00:32:34,742 --> 00:32:39,280
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Now, drivers, give Agent Sumner
your undivided attention.</font></b>

346
00:32:39,380 --> 00:32:42,771
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The items you'll need on your mission
are over here.</font></b>

347
00:32:43,684 --> 00:32:48,590
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">B camera, Revere 8 model 40 magazine,
Keystone Capri K-25, silver.</font></b>

348
00:32:48,890 --> 00:32:54,362
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Hollow-handle shaving brush. Complete set
of cipher tables on edible silver foil.</font></b>

349
00:32:54,462 --> 00:32:57,244
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Specialist photographic equipment.</font></b>

350
00:32:58,199 --> 00:33:01,949
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah, we...we get the idea. Thank you.</font></b>

351
00:33:13,281 --> 00:33:16,284
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Excuse me, Agent...Bosco. "Blasco".</font></b>

352
00:33:16,384 --> 00:33:18,052
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Sir.</font></b>

353
00:33:18,152 --> 00:33:22,291
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">There seems to be a subsection
to this list here.</font></b>

354
00:33:22,991 --> 00:33:24,926
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, most of this stuff
came from his studio,</font></b>

355
00:33:25,026 --> 00:33:27,795
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">but the rest is from the hotel
room he was holed up in.</font></b>

356
00:33:27,895 --> 00:33:30,364
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Where we found him.</font></b>

357
00:33:30,464 --> 00:33:32,800
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The hotel room you searched?</font></b>

358
00:33:32,900 --> 00:33:34,402
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, yeah.</font></b>

359
00:33:34,502 --> 00:33:38,035
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Can I see the warrant?
- The what?</font></b>

360
00:33:39,207 --> 00:33:41,709
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah, explain this to me.
There was a warrant.</font></b>

361
00:33:41,809 --> 00:33:45,379
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">There was a warrant. A civil detention writ
for the arrest of an alien,</font></b>

362
00:33:45,479 --> 00:33:49,017
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">but there was no search warrant
for suspicion of criminal activity.</font></b>

363
00:33:49,117 --> 00:33:52,253
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So the search and the evidence
that is the fruit of that search,</font></b>

364
00:33:52,353 --> 00:33:54,188
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">that's all tainted and should
not be admitted.</font></b>

365
00:33:54,288 --> 00:33:57,906
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">What protections is he due, Your Honor?
The man is not...the man is what?</font></b>

366
00:33:58,006 --> 00:34:01,713
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">He's Rudolf Ivanovich Abel.
He is a Soviet citizen.</font></b>

367
00:34:01,813 --> 00:34:03,364
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">He's not an American.</font></b>

368
00:34:03,464 --> 00:34:07,235
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">1886, Yick Wo v. Hopkins.</font></b>

369
00:34:07,335 --> 00:34:10,671
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The court held that even aliens,
in that case Chinese immigrants,</font></b>

370
00:34:10,771 --> 00:34:13,675
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">could not be held to answer for a crime
without due process of law,</font></b>

371
00:34:13,775 --> 00:34:16,310
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">including any alien that entered
the country illegally.</font></b>

372
00:34:16,410 --> 00:34:21,115
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The Department of Justice has its first
allegiance to the United States.</font></b>

373
00:34:21,215 --> 00:34:23,451
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I don't see how an alien,
if he's here illegally,</font></b>

374
00:34:23,551 --> 00:34:26,454
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">how he suffered deprivation of rights.</font></b>

375
00:34:26,554 --> 00:34:30,057
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Rights as what? An American?</font></b>

376
00:34:30,157 --> 00:34:34,727
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Rights as what, Counselor? We're
in a battle for civilization.</font></b>

377
00:34:34,827 --> 00:34:38,299
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">This Russian spy came here
to threaten our way of life.</font></b>

378
00:34:38,399 --> 00:34:40,401
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Now, I have a courtroom of people waiting.</font></b>

379
00:34:40,501 --> 00:34:44,655
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Get out there, sit beside the Russian.
Let's get this over and done with.</font></b>

380
00:34:44,755 --> 00:34:46,889
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And your motion is denied.</font></b>

381
00:34:49,643 --> 00:34:52,580
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">He should take some insurance out on himself.</font></b>

382
00:34:52,680 --> 00:34:55,696
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- How did we do?
- In there?</font></b>

383
00:34:57,785 --> 00:35:01,622
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Not too good. Apparently, you're
not an American citizen.</font></b>

384
00:35:01,722 --> 00:35:03,591
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">That's true.</font></b>

385
00:35:03,691 --> 00:35:08,079
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And according to your boss, you're
not a Soviet citizen either.</font></b>

386
00:35:08,179 --> 00:35:11,511
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, the boss isn't always right...</font></b>

387
00:35:12,099 --> 00:35:14,881
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">but he's always the boss.</font></b>

388
00:35:18,739 --> 00:35:20,941
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Do you never worry?</font></b>

389
00:35:21,041 --> 00:35:23,273
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Would it help?</font></b>

390
00:35:29,950 --> 00:35:32,165
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">All rise.</font></b>

391
00:35:33,621 --> 00:35:37,191
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">"I pledge allegiance to the flag"</font></b>

392
00:35:37,291 --> 00:35:40,394
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">"of the United States of America,"</font></b>

393
00:35:40,494 --> 00:35:44,498
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">"and to the republic for which it stands,"</font></b>

394
00:35:44,598 --> 00:35:49,203
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">"one nation under God, indivisible,"</font></b>

395
00:35:49,303 --> 00:35:52,019
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">"with liberty and justice for all."</font></b>

396
00:35:55,509 --> 00:35:59,859
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">First, you have to know what happens
when an atomic bomb explodes.</font></b>

397
00:36:01,983 --> 00:36:04,953
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">There is a bright flash,
brighter than the sun.</font></b>

398
00:36:05,353 --> 00:36:10,136
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It can smash in buildings, break windows
all over town.</font></b>

399
00:36:11,459 --> 00:36:16,764
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But if you duck and cover like Bert,
you will be much safer.</font></b>

400
00:36:16,864 --> 00:36:21,202
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">There are two kinds of attack, with warning
and without any warning.</font></b>

401
00:36:26,207 --> 00:36:29,177
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- What's going on in here?
- Okay, Dad, this is really important.</font></b>

402
00:36:29,277 --> 00:36:31,245
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">When the war begins,
the first thing they do</font></b>

403
00:36:31,345 --> 00:36:33,981
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">is cut off all the water
and all the electricity.</font></b>

404
00:36:34,081 --> 00:36:37,785
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So the first thing we should do is keep this filled,
use the shower in your room,</font></b>

405
00:36:37,885 --> 00:36:40,221
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">use the sink downstairs, the
garden hose outside...</font></b>

406
00:36:40,321 --> 00:36:42,223
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Those are good ideas.</font></b>

407
00:36:42,323 --> 00:36:47,507
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But, Roger, I don't see this as being something
you ever have to worry about.</font></b>

408
00:36:47,678 --> 00:36:49,100
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah, but when you hear the sirens,</font></b>

409
00:36:49,200 --> 00:36:52,167
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">there may not be enough time
to fill the tub and the sinks.</font></b>

410
00:36:53,167 --> 00:36:55,849
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Not gonna be any sirens.</font></b>

411
00:36:56,337 --> 00:36:57,405
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">What is this?</font></b>

412
00:36:57,605 --> 00:37:01,342
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">When the bomb comes, the Reds will aim
for the Empire State Building.</font></b>

413
00:37:01,442 --> 00:37:04,178
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But the bomb goes off at 10,000 feet up.</font></b>

414
00:37:04,278 --> 00:37:08,202
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">In Life magazine, it's called an airburst,
and if the bomb is 50 megatons,</font></b>

415
00:37:08,302 --> 00:37:13,855
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">the blast wave goes out and out and out
and melts everything from here to here.</font></b>

416
00:37:13,955 --> 00:37:16,657
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Including where we live. Here.</font></b>

417
00:37:16,757 --> 00:37:18,359
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah, right there.</font></b>

418
00:37:18,459 --> 00:37:21,763
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But, you know, Roger, no one is
dropping atomic bombs on us.</font></b>

419
00:37:21,963 --> 00:37:25,399
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But the Russians want to. You know
that Russian guy you're defending?</font></b>

420
00:37:25,499 --> 00:37:28,136
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">He's here to get things ready for
the guys who drop the bombs.</font></b>

421
00:37:28,236 --> 00:37:30,538
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No, no, he's not...not here for that.</font></b>

422
00:37:30,638 --> 00:37:33,941
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">He's not even Russian. He was born,
we think, in Northern England.</font></b>

423
00:37:34,041 --> 00:37:36,690
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But he's a spy for Russia.</font></b>

424
00:37:36,844 --> 00:37:38,579
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I don't even understand what you're doing.</font></b>

425
00:37:38,679 --> 00:37:40,948
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You're not a Communist, so
why are you defending one?</font></b>

426
00:37:41,048 --> 00:37:43,150
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, because it's my job.</font></b>

427
00:37:43,250 --> 00:37:45,382
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It never used to be.</font></b>

428
00:38:15,015 --> 00:38:19,520
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">In the case of the United States
of America versus Rudolf Abel,</font></b>

429
00:38:19,620 --> 00:38:24,125
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">as to the first count in the indictment,
how do you find the defendant?</font></b>

430
00:38:24,225 --> 00:38:26,994
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Guilty or not guilty?</font></b>

431
00:38:27,094 --> 00:38:28,930
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Guilty.</font></b>

432
00:38:29,030 --> 00:38:32,733
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- As to the second count?
- Guilty.</font></b>

433
00:38:32,833 --> 00:38:35,903
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- As to the third count?
- Guilty.</font></b>

434
00:38:36,003 --> 00:38:40,496
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Your Honor, I make a motion to set aside these
guilty verdicts against the weight of evidence.</font></b>

435
00:38:40,696 --> 00:38:41,809
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Denied.</font></b>

436
00:38:41,909 --> 00:38:45,879
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The jury is discharged. Thank you all.</font></b>

437
00:38:45,979 --> 00:38:47,857
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I would like to add that,
if I were one of you,</font></b>

438
00:38:47,957 --> 00:38:50,797
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I would've reached the same verdict.</font></b>

439
00:38:51,218 --> 00:38:54,783
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Sentencing will be...</font></b>

440
00:38:55,472 --> 00:38:58,065
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">November 15.</font></b>

441
00:39:05,966 --> 00:39:10,241
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The death sentence is not a foregone conclusion.
Don't worry.</font></b>

442
00:39:10,704 --> 00:39:14,269
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'm not afraid to die, Mr. Donovan.</font></b>

443
00:39:15,743 --> 00:39:17,578
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Although...</font></b>

444
00:39:17,678 --> 00:39:20,476
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">it wouldn't be my first choice.</font></b>

445
00:39:23,484 --> 00:39:26,700
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You left this behind.</font></b>

446
00:39:27,688 --> 00:39:29,985
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Oh, thank you.</font></b>

447
00:39:31,158 --> 00:39:33,722
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Oh, thank you very much.</font></b>

448
00:39:53,080 --> 00:39:56,812
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You've never asked me if
the charges were true.</font></b>

449
00:39:58,219 --> 00:40:02,308
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">If I am indeed a spy.</font></b>

450
00:40:03,190 --> 00:40:04,878
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">This is how we do it.</font></b>

451
00:40:04,978 --> 00:40:08,800
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The case against you matters.
Making them prove it matters.</font></b>

452
00:40:08,900 --> 00:40:12,466
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The fiction is...whether you did it
or not doesn't matter.</font></b>

453
00:40:12,566 --> 00:40:15,673
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The state has to prove it,
that you're a spy.</font></b>

454
00:40:15,773 --> 00:40:17,805
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So you're not curious?</font></b>

455
00:40:17,905 --> 00:40:22,142
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No, not really. I always assumed
you were an artist.</font></b>

456
00:40:22,242 --> 00:40:26,447
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">My wife, she's the artist.
She's a musician.</font></b>

457
00:40:26,547 --> 00:40:30,184
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">In the Children's Orchestra of Moscow.</font></b>

458
00:40:30,284 --> 00:40:33,654
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- What instrument?
- The harp.</font></b>

459
00:40:35,789 --> 00:40:38,190
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Then, she's an angel.</font></b>

460
00:40:47,701 --> 00:40:51,494
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Standing there like that, you remind me of a man
who used to come to our house</font></b>

461
00:40:51,594 --> 00:40:53,874
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">when I was young.</font></b>

462
00:40:54,274 --> 00:40:58,646
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">My father used to say, "watch this man".</font></b>

463
00:40:58,746 --> 00:41:02,277
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So I did, every time he came.</font></b>

464
00:41:02,377 --> 00:41:04,952
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And never once...</font></b>

465
00:41:05,052 --> 00:41:09,187
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">did he do anything remarkable.</font></b>

466
00:41:10,190 --> 00:41:12,455
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And I remind you of him?</font></b>

467
00:41:15,696 --> 00:41:19,533
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">This one time, I was about
the age of your son.</font></b>

468
00:41:19,633 --> 00:41:23,699
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Our house was overrun by
partisan border guards.</font></b>

469
00:41:26,540 --> 00:41:28,776
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Dozens of them.</font></b>

470
00:41:28,876 --> 00:41:30,944
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">My father was beaten, my mother was beaten,</font></b>

471
00:41:31,044 --> 00:41:35,408
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">and this man, my father's friend,
he was beaten.</font></b>

472
00:41:36,416 --> 00:41:39,234
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And I watched this man.</font></b>

473
00:41:41,555 --> 00:41:44,193
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Every time they hit him...</font></b>

474
00:41:45,158 --> 00:41:47,756
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">he stood back up again.</font></b>

475
00:41:49,062 --> 00:41:51,666
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So they hit him harder.</font></b>

476
00:41:52,800 --> 00:41:55,605
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Still, he got back to his feet.</font></b>

477
00:41:58,422 --> 00:42:02,989
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I think because of this they stopped
the beating. They let him live.</font></b>

478
00:42:10,851 --> 00:42:13,760
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I remember them saying it.</font></b>

479
00:42:20,427 --> 00:42:23,292
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It sort of means, like...</font></b>

480
00:42:25,032 --> 00:42:27,396
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">"standing man".</font></b>

481
00:42:30,337 --> 00:42:32,600
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Standing man.</font></b>

482
00:42:42,816 --> 00:42:45,452
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Hello, Jim!
- Millie, you're a vision.</font></b>

483
00:42:45,552 --> 00:42:48,055
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Mortie's busy getting kitted out.</font></b>

484
00:42:48,155 --> 00:42:50,452
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But come on in.</font></b>

485
00:42:51,058 --> 00:42:53,860
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Scotch, Jim?
- Oh, yes, please. Thank you.</font></b>

486
00:42:53,960 --> 00:42:56,497
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Just a drop of water.</font></b>

487
00:42:56,597 --> 00:43:00,401
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Your Honor.
- Hello, Jim. Just going out.</font></b>

488
00:43:00,501 --> 00:43:02,503
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Got a few minutes though.</font></b>

489
00:43:02,603 --> 00:43:06,860
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">March of Dimes thing. Millie is active.</font></b>

490
00:43:07,407 --> 00:43:08,809
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, thank you for seeing me.</font></b>

491
00:43:08,909 --> 00:43:12,980
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I just wanted to give you my two cents
on the sentencing.</font></b>

492
00:43:13,080 --> 00:43:16,116
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And I thought maybe I should
pester you at home</font></b>

493
00:43:16,216 --> 00:43:19,219
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">as not all of my points
are narrowly legal.</font></b>

494
00:43:19,319 --> 00:43:21,922
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah, well, it's that kind of case.</font></b>

495
00:43:22,022 --> 00:43:26,760
