659
00:56:51,247 --> 00:56:53,533
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Who we are.</font></b>

660
00:56:53,633 --> 00:56:58,137
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Is that not the greatest weapon
we have in this Cold War?</font></b>

661
00:56:58,237 --> 00:57:03,251
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Will we stand by our cause less resolutely
than he stands by his?</font></b>

662
00:59:46,706 --> 00:59:50,286
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The President announced that a NASA
weather plane disappeared</font></b>

663
00:59:50,386 --> 00:59:52,445
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">four days ago north of Turkey.</font></b>

664
00:59:52,545 --> 00:59:56,849
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And the Space Administration fears
that its pilot died in the crash.</font></b>

665
00:59:56,949 --> 01:00:01,574
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Radar showed the plane wandering off course
deep into Soviet territory</font></b>

666
01:00:01,674 --> 01:00:03,623
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">before contact was lost,</font></b>

667
01:00:03,723 --> 01:00:07,960
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">complicating any effort to recover it
or the remains of the pilot.</font></b>

668
01:00:08,060 --> 01:00:10,229
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Now to news out of Washington.</font></b>

669
01:00:10,329 --> 01:00:12,566
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">In a close vote today, the Supreme Court</font></b>

670
01:00:12,666 --> 01:00:16,669
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">affirmed the conviction of Russian spy
Rudolf Ivanovich Abel,</font></b>

671
01:00:16,769 --> 01:00:18,438
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">five votes to four.</font></b>

672
01:00:18,538 --> 01:00:22,622
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The case presented civil liberties issues,
according to the Russian's lawyer,</font></b>

673
01:00:22,722 --> 01:00:24,311
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">James B. Donovan.</font></b>

674
01:00:24,811 --> 01:00:27,013
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">When asked how he felt about today's loss,</font></b>

675
01:00:27,113 --> 01:00:30,717
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Mr. Donovan simply said, "tired".</font></b>

676
01:00:30,817 --> 01:00:34,686
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'll have more news for you
after this message.</font></b>

677
01:00:36,464 --> 01:00:38,348
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It's over.</font></b>

678
01:00:42,094 --> 01:00:43,863
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Marty.</font></b>

679
01:00:43,963 --> 01:00:46,566
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'll be damned if I can find the file
on that Prudential case.</font></b>

680
01:00:46,666 --> 01:00:50,269
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I...Mr. Watters had me move it
over to Jack Elwes's office.</font></b>

681
01:00:50,369 --> 01:00:53,139
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Along with the first draft of the appeal.
- He did?</font></b>

682
01:00:53,239 --> 01:00:57,805
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah, he redrafted and filed that last week
while you were in Washington.</font></b>

683
01:00:59,546 --> 01:01:03,449
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">How long have we been together? You act
as if I've never closed a deal.</font></b>

684
01:01:03,549 --> 01:01:06,386
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Set up a meeting. Someplace fancy.</font></b>

685
01:01:06,486 --> 01:01:10,356
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'm betting Mr. Young would like some of
the finer things New York has to offer.</font></b>

686
01:01:10,456 --> 01:01:13,321
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And I want you to give me the summary...</font></b>

687
01:01:30,910 --> 01:01:32,779
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Do you know anyone from Leipzig?</font></b>

688
01:01:32,879 --> 01:01:37,383
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">"Leipzig". Am I getting hate mail
from Germany now?</font></b>

689
01:01:37,483 --> 01:01:40,048
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">From East Germany.</font></b>

690
01:01:47,960 --> 01:01:49,862
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Is it your wife?</font></b>

691
01:01:49,962 --> 01:01:51,931
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No.</font></b>

692
01:01:52,031 --> 01:01:53,866
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No, no, no, no.</font></b>

693
01:01:54,066 --> 01:01:58,705
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">She pretends to be but it's
not even a good pretense.</font></b>

694
01:01:59,305 --> 01:02:04,143
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">"I'm taking this liberty to write to you after
having learned from the newspapers"</font></b>

695
01:02:04,243 --> 01:02:09,505
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">"about your most humane attitude
towards my beloved husband,"</font></b>

696
01:02:09,605 --> 01:02:11,918
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">"Rudolf Abel."</font></b>

697
01:02:12,318 --> 01:02:15,683
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And do I write back?</font></b>

698
01:02:17,457 --> 01:02:20,007
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah, yeah, yeah.</font></b>

699
01:02:22,595 --> 01:02:26,441
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">What's the next move when you
don't know what the game is?</font></b>

700
01:02:27,834 --> 01:02:30,632
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Francis Gary Powers...</font></b>

701
01:02:31,270 --> 01:02:36,376
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">On the strength of Article Two
of the U.S.S.R. law</font></b>

702
01:02:36,476 --> 01:02:40,279
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">on criminal responsibility
for state crimes</font></b>

703
01:02:40,379 --> 01:02:42,515
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">to 10 years of confinement</font></b>

704
01:02:42,615 --> 01:02:46,480
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">with the first three years
to be served in prison.</font></b>

705
01:02:47,587 --> 01:02:52,191
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The term of the punishment, including
preliminary detention,</font></b>

706
01:02:52,291 --> 01:02:54,694
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">shall be counted from May first,</font></b>

707
01:02:54,794 --> 01:02:57,614
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">nineteen hundred and sixty.</font></b>

708
01:03:22,455 --> 01:03:25,124
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Mr. Donovan, thank you so much for coming.</font></b>

709
01:03:25,224 --> 01:03:27,727
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It's a pleasure to meet you, Mr. Dulles.</font></b>

710
01:03:27,827 --> 01:03:30,196
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It's an honor, sir.</font></b>

711
01:03:30,296 --> 01:03:32,992
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Nescafe, cream,</font></b>

712
01:03:33,092 --> 01:03:34,576
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">two lumps.</font></b>

713
01:03:34,676 --> 01:03:36,636
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Thank you.</font></b>

714
01:03:36,736 --> 01:03:38,838
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Okay, this letter you received.</font></b>

715
01:03:38,938 --> 01:03:42,732
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Seems pretty clear that the Soviets
are making an overture here.</font></b>

716
01:03:42,742 --> 01:03:46,087
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">They're doing it through East Germany 'cause
they still don't want to acknowledge Abel</font></b>

717
01:03:46,088 --> 01:03:50,077
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">as a Soviet citizen, much less
a Soviet spy. So...</font></b>

718
01:03:50,516 --> 01:03:54,320
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Lot of fiction going on.
- Yes, sir, but to what end?</font></b>

719
01:03:54,420 --> 01:03:58,892
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">They got our guy, our spy pilot.
We've got their guy.</font></b>

720
01:04:00,760 --> 01:04:04,363
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Prisoner exchange, I think
that's what they're after.</font></b>

721
01:04:04,463 --> 01:04:06,632
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Which could hardly be a surprise
to you, Counselor.</font></b>

722
01:04:06,732 --> 01:04:09,461
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It's an eventuality that
I think you foresaw.</font></b>

723
01:04:09,561 --> 01:04:13,045
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yes, I sure did, and I'm so rarely right.</font></b>

724
01:04:13,145 --> 01:04:16,242
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, congratulations. Red letter day.</font></b>

725
01:04:16,342 --> 01:04:17,873
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Now...</font></b>

726
01:04:17,973 --> 01:04:20,280
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">we have our man over there. Powers.</font></b>

727
01:04:20,380 --> 01:04:24,316
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Good man, but with a head full
of classified information.</font></b>

728
01:04:24,416 --> 01:04:27,080
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Abel has a head full of classified
information, too,</font></b>

729
01:04:27,180 --> 01:04:30,523
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- but he hasn't given us a lick.
- And, sir, take it from me, he won't.</font></b>

730
01:04:30,623 --> 01:04:33,225
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yes, we know that, but the Russians don't.</font></b>

731
01:04:33,325 --> 01:04:35,748
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">They want their man back before he cracks.</font></b>

732
01:04:36,028 --> 01:04:40,332
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And we want Powers back
for the same reasons.</font></b>

733
01:04:42,501 --> 01:04:47,273
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I think you are saying, sir, that there might
be a happy ending for everyone.</font></b>

734
01:04:47,373 --> 01:04:51,561
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yes, if we...indulge their fiction.</font></b>

735
01:04:58,517 --> 01:05:00,486
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We want you to negotiate the swap</font></b>

736
01:05:00,586 --> 01:05:04,440
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">because you're a private citizen,
so it's not governments talking.</font></b>

737
01:05:04,540 --> 01:05:06,576
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">They don't acknowledge Abel
as a Soviet citizen,</font></b>

738
01:05:06,676 --> 01:05:10,430
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">and we don't acknowledge East Germany
as a sovereign country.</font></b>

739
01:05:10,530 --> 01:05:14,700
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We haven't recognized East Berlin since
it was annexed by the Soviets in '45.</font></b>

740
01:05:14,800 --> 01:05:17,837
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So I act as a negotiator, representing...</font></b>

741
01:05:17,937 --> 01:05:20,773
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You're not representing anybody.
Not a government official.</font></b>

742
01:05:20,873 --> 01:05:23,175
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You have no official standing.</font></b>

743
01:05:23,275 --> 01:05:26,395
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- So, some fiction on our side as well.
- Correct.</font></b>

744
01:05:26,495 --> 01:05:29,949
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Which means, of course, you can't
rely on any acknowledgment</font></b>

745
01:05:30,049 --> 01:05:32,652
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">or help if things go south.</font></b>

746
01:05:32,752 --> 01:05:37,051
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">CIA can't be responsible. We
can't be embarrassed.</font></b>

747
01:05:38,891 --> 01:05:41,460
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Where do they want this negotiation
to take place?</font></b>

748
01:05:41,560 --> 01:05:43,996
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- There.
- "There"?</font></b>

749
01:05:44,296 --> 01:05:46,560
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">East Berlin.</font></b>

750
01:05:47,667 --> 01:05:50,119
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, isn't East Berlin getting rather...</font></b>

751
01:05:50,219 --> 01:05:53,567
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Oh, yes, the place is getting complicated.</font></b>

752
01:05:54,306 --> 01:05:56,703
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah, complicated.</font></b>

753
01:05:58,377 --> 01:06:01,614
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The Soviet side has been setting up checkpoints
for the past few months</font></b>

754
01:06:01,714 --> 01:06:05,618
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">to try to stop people hemorrhaging to the
Western sectors, and it hasn't worked.</font></b>

755
01:06:06,018 --> 01:06:09,822
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We have intelligence to suggest that
they may go one step further</font></b>

756
01:06:09,922 --> 01:06:13,520
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">and wall off the entire Eastern sector.</font></b>

757
01:06:17,897 --> 01:06:20,316
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Okay, that's it in a nutshell.</font></b>

758
01:06:20,416 --> 01:06:22,968
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The decision is entirely yours.</font></b>

759
01:06:23,068 --> 01:06:26,799
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You need time to kick it around.</font></b>

760
01:06:32,111 --> 01:06:34,080
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No.</font></b>

761
01:06:34,480 --> 01:06:38,550
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- No, I don't.
- Well, fine. Fine.</font></b>

762
01:06:38,650 --> 01:06:43,426
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Best that this all remains confidential.
Let's not discuss any of this with, uh,</font></b>

763
01:06:43,526 --> 01:06:46,058
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Mary or with anyone else.</font></b>

764
01:06:46,158 --> 01:06:50,096
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Share the correspondence only with us. Let
us know what they want to do and when.</font></b>

765
01:06:50,196 --> 01:06:52,865
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I've got no client, no wife, no country.</font></b>

766
01:06:52,965 --> 01:06:56,268
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Don't know what I'm doing
or when or who for.</font></b>

767
01:06:56,368 --> 01:06:59,772
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You're doing it for your country, but
your country doesn't know that yet.</font></b>

768
01:06:59,872 --> 01:07:02,909
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">What about my client, the other person
in this equation? My guy?</font></b>

769
01:07:03,009 --> 01:07:06,612
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Your guy? You mean the Russian? He's
not your guy anymore, Counselor.</font></b>

770
01:07:06,712 --> 01:07:09,982
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Your guy is Francis Gary Powers now.</font></b>

771
01:07:10,082 --> 01:07:13,002
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">What do I tell Rudolf Abel?</font></b>

772
01:07:13,102 --> 01:07:15,549
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Tell him not to drop dead.</font></b>

773
01:09:07,433 --> 01:09:09,496
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Professor?</font></b>

774
01:09:14,506 --> 01:09:16,308
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Professor?</font></b>

775
01:09:16,408 --> 01:09:20,412
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Papa went to university. You
shouldn't be here, Frederic.</font></b>

776
01:09:20,512 --> 01:09:24,983
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- They're having classes today?
- He went to see. That's where he goes.</font></b>

777
01:09:25,083 --> 01:09:28,020
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- What are you doing here?
- I came to get you and your father.</font></b>

778
01:09:28,120 --> 01:09:30,286
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You have to come with me. You
might not get out tomorrow.</font></b>

779
01:09:30,386 --> 01:09:34,051
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Just...just leave?
- Yes. Yes, yes, yes, leave. Right now.</font></b>

780
01:10:05,420 --> 01:10:07,623
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Go back. Go back.</font></b>

781
01:10:07,723 --> 01:10:09,892
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'll be okay, I'm American. Go back.</font></b>

782
01:10:09,992 --> 01:10:13,424
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Go back to your father's. We'll
find another way. Go.</font></b>

783
01:10:18,267 --> 01:10:21,336
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Hey!
- So, hi.</font></b>

784
01:10:24,656 --> 01:10:29,044
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Papers, please.
- Ich bin student Frederic Pryor.</font></b>

785
01:10:29,144 --> 01:10:32,075
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yes, student.</font></b>

786
01:10:41,657 --> 01:10:45,189
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">My name's Frederic Pryor.
I'm an economics student.</font></b>

787
01:10:46,095 --> 01:10:51,056
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">See? It's my dissertation. My thesis.</font></b>

788
01:10:52,468 --> 01:10:54,169
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You see? Look, look.</font></b>

789
01:10:54,269 --> 01:10:58,349
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">"The foreign trade system of the
European Communist nations."</font></b>

790
01:11:02,844 --> 01:11:04,582
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It was a lot of work.</font></b>

791
01:11:11,887 --> 01:11:14,216
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No, that's my only copy.</font></b>

792
01:11:15,957 --> 01:11:17,932
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No!</font></b>

793
01:11:19,578 --> 01:11:21,013
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Tell me something.</font></b>

794
01:11:21,263 --> 01:11:25,601
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It came up at the last minute.
They have offices in London.</font></b>

795
01:11:25,701 --> 01:11:28,734
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">These clients. Not my idea.</font></b>

796
01:11:28,834 --> 01:11:31,273
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Scotland, this fishing expedition.</font></b>

797
01:11:31,373 --> 01:11:35,841
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- What kind of fishing trip, Jim?
- Salmon fishing.</font></b>

798
01:11:36,178 --> 01:11:38,247
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Just tell me that you're not
gonna be in any danger,</font></b>

799
01:11:38,347 --> 01:11:42,051
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">that this is just a routine business trip,
and I won't worry.</font></b>

800
01:11:42,151 --> 01:11:44,497
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I need my passport.</font></b>

801
01:11:48,507 --> 01:11:52,836
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Just give me something to hold on to.
I don't even care if it's the truth.</font></b>

802
01:11:53,895 --> 01:11:56,460
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'm doing this for us.</font></b>

803
01:12:18,987 --> 01:12:23,625
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Mr. Michener, here, is your Berlin escort.
He's an attache with the U.S. embassy.</font></b>

804
01:12:23,725 --> 01:12:25,961
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So, it's gotten goddamn complicated.</font></b>

805
01:12:26,061 --> 01:12:29,266
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">As you know, the last letter from Mrs. Abel,
whoever she is, talks about a lawyer</font></b>

806
01:12:29,366 --> 01:12:32,301
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">in East Berlin, Mr. Vogel, whoever he is,
representing her interests, she says.</font></b>

807
01:12:32,401 --> 01:12:35,737
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah, Vogel says he's gone to the
Russian embassy in East Berlin</font></b>

808
01:12:35,837 --> 01:12:38,907
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">and they may be ready to
trade Abel for Powers.</font></b>

809
01:12:39,007 --> 01:12:41,510
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But no one knows who's who, but essentially
they're all Russian, right?</font></b>

810
01:12:41,610 --> 01:12:44,146
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Well, Soviet.
- Well, we think so.</font></b>

811
01:12:44,246 --> 01:12:46,811
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">What do you mean? Could we
turn up the heat in here?</font></b>

812
01:12:46,911 --> 01:12:48,452
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No, it's...</font></b>

813
01:12:49,483 --> 01:12:52,955
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">There's a wrinkle. They might
try to throw you a curveball.</font></b>

814
01:12:53,055 --> 01:12:56,158
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Try and get you to accept another prisoner
other than Powers.</font></b>

815
01:12:56,258 --> 01:12:57,626
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Another American?</font></b>

816
01:12:58,026 --> 01:13:02,030
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The...East German Stasi picked up an American student.
Frederic Pryor.</font></b>

817
01:13:02,130 --> 01:13:04,633
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The kid they found on the wrong side
of the Wall.</font></b>

818
01:13:04,733 --> 01:13:08,104
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">He's a grad student out of Yale. Came
over here to study economics.</font></b>

819
01:13:08,204 --> 01:13:12,274
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So, they're making noises about
trying this kid for espionage.</font></b>

820
01:13:12,374 --> 01:13:15,093
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Grave offense, capital crime. Well.</font></b>

821
01:13:15,193 --> 01:13:19,615
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Vogel got in touch with us,
said he represents Pryor.</font></b>

822
01:13:19,715 --> 01:13:24,786
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Wait a minute. Vogel represents
Mrs. Abel and this...this kid?</font></b>

823
01:13:24,986 --> 01:13:27,189
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah, he's busy.</font></b>

824
01:13:27,289 --> 01:13:31,109
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, so, what is he? Vogel, is he...East German
or is he Russian?</font></b>

825
01:13:31,210 --> 01:13:33,362
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, try to figure it out
when you meet him.</font></b>

826
01:13:33,462 --> 01:13:35,814
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">At Russian embassy, East Berlin, noon tomorrow.</font></b>

827
01:13:35,914 --> 01:13:38,300
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Hoffman will show you how to get there.</font></b>

828
01:13:38,400 --> 01:13:42,471
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Wait, show me how to get there?
I'm gonna have an escort. Right?</font></b>

829
01:13:42,571 --> 01:13:45,947
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, that was the plan but, like I said,
there's a wrinkle. I won't be taking you.</font></b>

830
01:13:46,047 --> 01:13:50,271
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Decision's been made. No U.S. government personnel
are to cross the border until further notice.</font></b>

831
01:13:50,272 --> 01:13:50,900
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">How come?</font></b>

832
01:13:50,903 --> 01:13:53,332
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It's too dangerous. Yeah, the East Germans
grabbed this kid.</font></b>

833
01:13:53,432 --> 01:13:56,602
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">There's a degree of impunity
that we had not anticipated.</font></b>

834
01:13:57,152 --> 01:14:00,555
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The point is that the East German agenda
and the Russian agenda</font></b>

835
01:14:00,655 --> 01:14:01,990
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">may not be the same thing.</font></b>

836
01:14:02,090 --> 01:14:05,777
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Try and figure it out and act accordingly.
And try to make a deal. Powers for Abel.</font></b>

837
01:14:05,877 --> 01:14:08,814
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, what about this college kid, Pryor?</font></b>

838
01:14:09,464 --> 01:14:11,250
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Don't fall for that.</font></b>

839
01:14:11,350 --> 01:14:14,130
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We can get him out another time.
Powers is the whole ball game.</font></b>

840
01:14:37,058 --> 01:14:39,361
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Where's your room?</font></b>

841
01:14:39,461 --> 01:14:41,892
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'll be staying at the Hilton.</font></b>

842
01:14:42,964 --> 01:14:44,995
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It's not far.</font></b>

843
01:14:46,134 --> 01:14:48,437
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">This is a number here in West Berlin.</font></b>

844
01:14:48,737 --> 01:14:51,334
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Memorize it and give it back to me.</font></b>

845
01:14:51,640 --> 01:14:54,070
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No, no. I mean, now.</font></b>

846
01:14:55,410 --> 01:14:59,715
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The Soviets keep cutting the international lines
but local calls are okay.</font></b>

847
01:15:00,015 --> 01:15:02,507
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Someone will pick up day and night.</font></b>

848
01:15:10,292 --> 01:15:13,403
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Now, this docket attached to
your passport will serve</font></b>

849
01:15:13,503 --> 01:15:17,060
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">as your ticket into and out of
the Eastern Soviet sector.</font></b>

850
01:15:17,766 --> 01:15:20,931
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The meeting with Vogel is set
for noon tomorrow.</font></b>

851
01:15:26,308 --> 01:15:28,093
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">There are only a few routes left
to the East.</font></b>

852
01:15:28,193 --> 01:15:30,629
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You take the S-Bahn, the station
we showed you on the way in.</font></b>

853
01:15:30,729 --> 01:15:32,981
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You're gonna get off at the Friedrichstrasse station here</font></b>

854
01:15:33,081 --> 01:15:36,017
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">and walk to the Soviet embassy
on Unter den Linden here.</font></b>

855
01:15:36,117 --> 01:15:38,387
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Look at the map now. You
shouldn't take it with you.</font></b>

856
01:15:38,487 --> 01:15:42,608
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You're looking at a map, you're an American,
you're a spy. You could well be detained.</font></b>

857
01:15:42,708 --> 01:15:47,564
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Just avoid interacting with people generally.
You don't belong, so don't stick out.</font></b>

858
01:15:47,664 --> 01:15:50,065
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Food is scarce over there and things
have started to fall apart.</font></b>

859
01:15:50,165 --> 01:15:54,303
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">There are gangs, and rule of law is
less firmly established over there.</font></b>

860
01:15:54,403 --> 01:15:56,338
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And definitely stay away from the Wall.</font></b>

861
01:15:56,438 --> 01:15:58,907
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">On their side, there's a line cleared
of buildings along the Wall.</font></b>

862
01:15:59,007 --> 01:16:01,877
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">They call it the "Death Line".
Cross it and you'll be shot.</font></b>

863
01:16:01,977 --> 01:16:04,846
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Is there any outcome here where
I'm not either detained or shot?</font></b>

864
01:16:04,946 --> 01:16:07,282
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Don't worry too much about
what Michener said.</font></b>

865
01:16:07,382 --> 01:16:09,551
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No, I'm worried about what you're saying.</font></b>

866
01:16:09,651 --> 01:16:13,321
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">This kid, Pryor, that the East
Germans have, how old is he?</font></b>

867
01:16:13,421 --> 01:16:17,667
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Twenty-five. Why?
- Same age as Dougie.</font></b>

868
01:16:19,160 --> 01:16:22,785
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Who?
- An associate of mine.</font></b>

869
01:16:24,233 --> 01:16:26,666
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Frederic Pryor.</font></b>

870
01:18:02,864 --> 01:18:05,195
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Okay, okay, okay.</font></b>

871
01:18:52,253 --> 01:18:53,985
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Danke.</font></b>

872
01:19:49,905 --> 01:19:53,671
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So, we apologize...</font></b>

873
01:19:53,771 --> 01:19:56,624
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">if this offends.</font></b>

874
01:20:02,716 --> 01:20:04,580
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Coat?</font></b>

875
01:20:22,637 --> 01:20:24,434
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Okay.</font></b>

876
01:21:16,525 --> 01:21:19,544
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Do you understand English?
- Yes, sir.</font></b>

877
01:21:19,644 --> 01:21:21,930
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'm James Donovan. I'm here
to meet a Mr. Vogel.</font></b>

878
01:21:22,030 --> 01:21:23,965
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Mr. Vogel.
- He doesn't work here.</font></b>

879
01:21:24,065 --> 01:21:26,885
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'm just supposed to meet him.
That's all I know.</font></b>

880
01:21:49,757 --> 01:21:51,860
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Mr. Donovan!</font></b>

881
01:21:51,960 --> 01:21:54,490
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So we finally meet you.</font></b>

882
01:21:55,663 --> 01:21:58,466
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- I'm Helen Abel. How is our husband?
- Oh. He's fine.</font></b>

883
01:21:58,566 --> 01:22:01,736
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- How is my Rudolf?
- As good as can be expected.</font></b>

884
01:22:01,836 --> 01:22:04,372
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And we will get him back, yes?</font></b>

885
01:22:04,472 --> 01:22:07,308
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- This is our daughter.
- How do you do?</font></b>

886
01:22:07,408 --> 01:22:08,743
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Lydia.</font></b>

887
01:22:08,843 --> 01:22:10,979
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Are you Mr. Vogel?</font></b>

888
01:22:11,079 --> 01:22:14,155
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No, no, no! I'm not Vogel.</font></b>

889
01:22:14,355 --> 01:22:16,579
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'm cousin Drews.</font></b>

890
01:22:17,318 --> 01:22:20,196
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- This is Rudolf's beloved cousin Drews.
- Yes, cousin Drews.</font></b>

891
01:22:20,296 --> 01:22:23,091
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- I am cousin Drews.
- Cousin Drews, yes.</font></b>

892
01:22:23,191 --> 01:22:25,721
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'm Helen Abel.</font></b>

893
01:22:28,363 --> 01:22:30,226
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">When will you see him?</font></b>

894
01:22:31,099 --> 01:22:33,134
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">When will your government release him?</font></b>

895
01:22:33,234 --> 01:22:37,038
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, I'm a little...lost here. I'm
supposed to meet a Mr. Vogel.</font></b>

896
01:22:37,138 --> 01:22:39,174
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Oh, Mr. Vogel is our lawyer.</font></b>

897
01:22:39,274 --> 01:22:43,044
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So we were supposed to negotiate, the exchange.</font></b>

898
01:22:43,144 --> 01:22:45,847
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- To bring Rudolf here?
- Yes, yes, to bring him here.</font></b>

899
01:22:45,947 --> 01:22:48,617
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But it doesn't happen unilaterally,
do you understand?</font></b>

900
01:22:48,717 --> 01:22:51,738
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It has to be an exchange.</font></b>

901
01:22:54,055 --> 01:22:55,519
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Not here?</font></b>

902
01:23:15,643 --> 01:23:18,396
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Mr. Donovan?
- Mr. Vogel.</font></b>

903
01:23:18,496 --> 01:23:22,417
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No, no, no. Goodness. My name is Schischkin.
Ivan Schischkin.</font></b>

904
01:23:22,517 --> 01:23:25,853
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'm the second secretary
of the Soviet embassy.</font></b>

905
01:23:25,953 --> 01:23:28,857
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It wouldn't be appropriate
for Mr. Vogel to join us.</font></b>

906
01:23:28,957 --> 01:23:31,159
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">He is a German national.</font></b>

907
01:23:31,259 --> 01:23:33,394
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So you aren't here to...</font></b>

908
01:23:33,494 --> 01:23:36,998
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">To facilitate this meeting.</font></b>

909
01:23:37,990 --> 01:23:42,203
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Perhaps Mrs. Abel would like to
compose herself privately?</font></b>

910
01:23:42,303 --> 01:23:46,187
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And let Mr. Donovan and myself to talk?</font></b>

911
01:23:47,675 --> 01:23:49,755
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Thank you.</font></b>

912
01:23:58,386 --> 01:24:01,022
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- So, I'm confused.
- Yes.</font></b>

913
01:24:01,122 --> 01:24:05,794
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I don't care who I talk to if it's about
an exchange of personnel.</font></b>

914
01:24:05,894 --> 01:24:09,627
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Are you the person to talk to?
- Yes, yes, yes, of course.</font></b>

915
01:24:09,727 --> 01:24:14,320
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We should talk. Please, have a seat, Mr. Donovan.</font></b>

916
01:24:15,003 --> 01:24:16,938
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">How did you arrive to the Eastern sector?</font></b>

917
01:24:17,038 --> 01:24:20,041
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- The train. The S-Bahn.
- And you were alone?</font></b>

918
01:24:20,141 --> 01:24:21,609
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah.</font></b>

919
01:24:21,709 --> 01:24:24,813
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And you are credentialed?</font></b>

920
01:24:24,913 --> 01:24:28,549
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Now, you must know about me, sir.
I'm a private citizen.</font></b>

921
01:24:28,649 --> 01:24:30,651
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'm a lawyer in Brooklyn
in the United States,</font></b>

922
01:24:30,751 --> 01:24:35,724
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">and I've taken time out of my busy schedule
to help my client, Rudolf Abel.</font></b>

923
01:24:35,824 --> 01:24:40,520
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'm authorized to arrange
an exchange of Abel</font></b>

924
01:24:40,521 --> 01:24:42,662
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">for Francis Gary Powers.</font></b>

925
01:24:42,663 --> 01:24:45,979
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">This is a full pardon of Abel
that will be signed</font></b>

926
01:24:46,079 --> 01:24:48,803
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">when the exchange actually takes place.</font></b>

927
01:24:48,903 --> 01:24:50,305
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">This is the only reason I'm here.</font></b>

928
01:24:50,405 --> 01:24:54,342
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I hope and expect to make
this arrangement quickly.</font></b>

929
01:24:54,442 --> 01:24:57,773
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Abel for Francis Gary Powers...</font></b>

930
01:24:58,313 --> 01:25:01,044
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">and Frederic Pryor.</font></b>

931
01:25:02,691 --> 01:25:07,117
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- We don't have Pryor.
- No? You don't?</font></b>

932
01:25:08,723 --> 01:25:11,326
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I've heard of Pryor, but he's held</font></b>

933
01:25:11,426 --> 01:25:14,295
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">by the German Democratic Republic,</font></b>

934
01:25:14,395 --> 01:25:18,166
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">not by the Union of Soviet Socialist Republics.</font></b>

935
01:25:18,266 --> 01:25:21,069
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, I'll tell you the first problem.</font></b>

936
01:25:21,169 --> 01:25:23,805
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The names of your countries are too long.</font></b>

937
01:25:25,954 --> 01:25:28,166
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yes, yes.</font></b>

938
01:25:28,476 --> 01:25:30,464
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">If we release Powers,</font></b>

939
01:25:30,564 --> 01:25:34,611
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">it is only to promote a goodwill
between our countries.</font></b>

940
01:25:35,183 --> 01:25:38,949
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So, it cannot be an exchange.</font></b>

941
01:25:41,255 --> 01:25:45,193
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Perhaps...perhaps you could release Abel</font></b>

942
01:25:45,293 --> 01:25:48,746
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">as a token of goodwill to our friends
in Germany, and then,</font></b>

943
01:25:48,846 --> 01:25:53,120
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">some months later, we would release Powers.
There is an idea.</font></b>

944
01:25:53,220 --> 01:25:57,485
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No. That just won't work for us at all. See,
we need this to be an exchange.</font></b>

945
01:25:57,585 --> 01:26:00,775
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You can call it what you want,
but an exchange it must be.</font></b>

946
01:26:00,875 --> 01:26:04,045
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We can have Abel here within 48 hours.</font></b>

947
01:26:04,145 --> 01:26:08,831
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We need Powers at the same time
we give you Abel.</font></b>

948
01:26:10,717 --> 01:26:12,420
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">This is...</font></b>

949
01:26:12,520 --> 01:26:16,036
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Can we call this the "impatient plan"?</font></b>

950
01:26:16,457 --> 01:26:19,300
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, you can call it whatever you want.</font></b>

951
01:26:20,361 --> 01:26:24,332
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I can relay your impatient plan to Moscow,
see what they say...</font></b>

952
01:26:24,432 --> 01:26:28,870
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But they will wonder why so impatient.</font></b>

953
01:26:28,970 --> 01:26:33,374
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Because I have a cold. And I don't live
in Berlin and I want to go home.</font></b>

954
01:26:33,474 --> 01:26:36,817
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">They will think, "well, the Americans..."</font></b>

955
01:26:36,917 --> 01:26:40,448
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">"must have gotten all the information
that Abel had to give."</font></b>

956
01:26:40,548 --> 01:26:43,985
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">"And now they're impatient to trade him,"</font></b>

957
01:26:44,085 --> 01:26:47,255
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">"hoping to get in return this man, Powers,"</font></b>

958
01:26:47,355 --> 01:26:52,621
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">"that, perhaps, has not yet given up all
the information that he has to give."</font></b>

959
01:26:53,061 --> 01:26:56,327
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">This is not an equitable trade, sir.</font></b>

960
01:26:56,864 --> 01:27:00,468
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But what you're saying is, if Powers
has given up everything he knows,</font></b>

961
01:27:00,568 --> 01:27:02,737
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">then Moscow would trade?</font></b>

962
01:27:02,837 --> 01:27:05,273
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Why wouldn't they?</font></b>

963
01:27:05,373 --> 01:27:08,343
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">As for Abel, if he dies
in an American prison,</font></b>

964
01:27:08,443 --> 01:27:11,605
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">the next Russian operative who gets caught
might think twice</font></b>

965
01:27:11,705 --> 01:27:14,026
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">about keeping his mouth shut.
And you never know.</font></b>

966
01:27:14,126 --> 01:27:17,886
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Abel might want to see the sky again.</font></b>

967
01:27:18,586 --> 01:27:22,918
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And decide to trade Russian secrets
for small American favors.</font></b>

968
01:27:25,660 --> 01:27:27,662
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">How can we know this?</font></b>

969
01:27:27,762 --> 01:27:31,165
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We little men, we just do our jobs.</font></b>

970
01:27:31,265 --> 01:27:34,337
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Like Lieutenant Powers. He's just a pilot.</font></b>

971
01:27:36,537 --> 01:27:38,570
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">He was making photographs</font></b>

972
01:27:38,670 --> 01:27:41,871
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">from 70,000 feet when he was shot
from the sky.</font></b>

973
01:27:42,543 --> 01:27:44,845
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">People in my country consider this...</font></b>

974
01:27:45,245 --> 01:27:46,915
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">an act of war.</font></b>

975
01:27:48,916 --> 01:27:51,619
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We have to get off this merry-go-round, sir.</font></b>

976
01:27:51,719 --> 01:27:55,876
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The next mistake our countries make
could be the last one.</font></b>

977
01:27:56,190 --> 01:28:01,198
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We need to have the conversation
our governments can't.</font></b>

978
01:28:05,800 --> 01:28:08,152
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I will ask Moscow.</font></b>

979
01:28:08,252 --> 01:28:11,116
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Who knows what they will say.</font></b>

980
01:28:12,106 --> 01:28:15,627
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">There are a lot of people, Mr. Donovan,
who doesn't want this...</font></b>

981
01:28:15,727 --> 01:28:18,939
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">exchange to ever take place.</font></b>

982
01:28:20,715 --> 01:28:23,885
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Can you come back tomorrow
to discuss their answer?</font></b>

983
01:28:23,985 --> 01:28:26,821
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Powers for Abel.
- And Frederic Pryor.</font></b>

984
01:28:26,921 --> 01:28:31,127
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">As I said, Pryor is in the hands
of the organs of State Security</font></b>

985
01:28:31,227 --> 01:28:35,796
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- of the German Democratic Republic.
- I'm confident you can make arrangements.</font></b>

986
01:28:35,896 --> 01:28:39,367
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I am merely a secretary in the embassy
of foreign power.</font></b>

987
01:28:39,467 --> 01:28:40,635
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Okay.</font></b>

988
01:28:40,735 --> 01:28:44,372
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You have to see Mr. Vogel.
I'll give you his address.</font></b>

989
01:28:44,472 --> 01:28:48,943
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- There actually is a Mr. Vogel?
- Why would you imagine otherwise?</font></b>

990
01:28:49,843 --> 01:28:51,846
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It's a short cab ride.</font></b>

991
01:28:51,946 --> 01:28:54,715
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And please, Mr. Donovan,</font></b>

992
01:28:54,815 --> 01:28:57,647
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">wear an overcoat in this weather.</font></b>

993
01:28:58,052 --> 01:29:00,750
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I had mine stolen from me.</font></b>

994
01:29:00,888 --> 01:29:05,321
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">What do you expect? It was from
Saks Fifth Avenue.</font></b>

995
01:29:05,960 --> 01:29:08,057
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Wasn't it?</font></b>

996
01:29:15,403 --> 01:29:18,239
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Mr. Donovan.
- Mr. Vogel.</font></b>

997
01:29:18,339 --> 01:29:20,241
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Please come in.</font></b>

998
01:29:20,341 --> 01:29:21,938
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Danke.</font></b>

999
01:29:24,812 --> 01:29:27,025
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Sorry about the embassy.</font></b>

1000
01:29:28,549 --> 01:29:31,382
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But the Soviets decided not to host me.</font></b>

1001
01:29:32,386 --> 01:29:34,022
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Very irritating.</font></b>

1002
01:29:34,122 --> 01:29:37,492
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I am still trying to grasp each party's...</font></b>

1003
01:29:37,592 --> 01:29:39,093
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Status?</font></b>

1004
01:29:39,193 --> 01:29:43,300
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yes. And interest in the proceedings.</font></b>

1005
01:29:43,531 --> 01:29:47,910
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It's a new world. All very
disorienting, isn't it?</font></b>

1006
01:29:58,045 --> 01:30:00,676
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Let me tell you what I have to offer.</font></b>

1007
01:30:02,550 --> 01:30:06,514
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'm a good friend..."friend".
No, he's older.</font></b>

1008
01:30:06,614 --> 01:30:10,925
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">"Protege"? Of the attorney general
of the German Democratic Republic.</font></b>

1009
01:30:11,025 --> 01:30:13,322
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Sit down, please.</font></b>

1010
01:30:15,529 --> 01:30:19,367
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">This unfortunate, Frederic Pryor...</font></b>

1011
01:30:19,467 --> 01:30:22,384
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">he was in the wrong place
at the wrong time.</font></b>

1012
01:30:22,484 --> 01:30:25,706
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But every accident, properly viewed,</font></b>

1013
01:30:25,806 --> 01:30:28,731
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- is an opportunity, isn't it, Mr. Donovan?
- Well...</font></b>

1014
01:30:28,831 --> 01:30:33,247
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Your country refuses to recognize
the German Democratic Republic.</font></b>

1015
01:30:33,347 --> 01:30:38,321
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">They prefer to make up stories that the GDR
doesn't exist, for instance.</font></b>

1016
01:30:39,553 --> 01:30:40,922
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Sorry.</font></b>

1017
01:30:41,422 --> 01:30:46,460
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">As a means of forcing your government's
recognition of this real place, sir,</font></b>

1018
01:30:46,560 --> 01:30:49,964
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">in which you find yourself, the GDR,</font></b>

1019
01:30:50,064 --> 01:30:52,266
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">the attorney general is happy
to negotiate with you</font></b>

1020
01:30:52,366 --> 01:30:56,003
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">as a representative of your government
for Mr. Pryor's return.</font></b>

1021
01:30:56,103 --> 01:31:00,336
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Mr. Vogel, I'm not here as a representative
of my government.</font></b>

1022
01:31:02,810 --> 01:31:04,874
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Alright.</font></b>

1023
01:31:06,714 --> 01:31:08,916
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I think that's childish, Mr. Donovan.</font></b>

1024
01:31:09,016 --> 01:31:11,615
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, I have no official status.</font></b>

1025
01:31:11,715 --> 01:31:15,873
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Fine. You do not represent the USA,
I do not represent the GDR.</font></b>

1026
01:31:15,973 --> 01:31:19,127
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">My client is Lydia Abel, Rudolf's wife.
And I have also...</font></b>

1027
01:31:19,227 --> 01:31:22,908
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Lydia is the daughter.
Helen is the wife.</font></b>

1028
01:31:27,735 --> 01:31:29,565
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well...</font></b>

1029
01:31:30,338 --> 01:31:35,554
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I am prepared to offer Frederic Pryor's
exchange for Rudolf Abel's.</font></b>

1030
01:31:36,677 --> 01:31:39,947
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Then let's be clear. We will
produce Rudolf Abel.</font></b>

1031
01:31:40,047 --> 01:31:43,951
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You will produce, at the same time,
the student, Pryor.</font></b>

1032
01:31:44,051 --> 01:31:46,954
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- At the same time?
- Absolutely.</font></b>

1033
01:31:47,054 --> 01:31:52,621
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The exchange on offer is a Russian
at the end of his life...</font></b>

1034
01:31:53,928 --> 01:31:57,632
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">for an American student
at the start of his.</font></b>

1035
01:32:03,337 --> 01:32:06,340
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Schischkin? He's not an embassy secretary.</font></b>

1036
01:32:06,440 --> 01:32:09,043
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Ivan Schischkin is the KGB's
chief in western Europe.</font></b>

1037
01:32:09,143 --> 01:32:14,828
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, whatever he is, he's relaying
our proposal to Moscow and...</font></b>

1038
01:32:15,616 --> 01:32:19,471
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">they'll decide. Could I borrow a coat?
I lost mine.</font></b>

1039
01:32:19,571 --> 01:32:24,048
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- How did you lose your coat?
- You know, spy stuff.</font></b>

1040
01:32:25,059 --> 01:32:28,296
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- I'll get you another coat.
- Good, because...</font></b>

1041
01:32:28,396 --> 01:32:31,565
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So who is...who is this Vogel?</font></b>

1042
01:32:31,665 --> 01:32:35,703
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Him, we don't know. He might be
what you said he said he is.</font></b>

1043
01:32:35,803 --> 01:32:40,708
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Friend of the attorney general. Just some guy
the GDR tapped to handle this.</font></b>

1044
01:32:40,808 --> 01:32:45,213
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Sounds like the East Germans are
fighting for a place at our table.</font></b>

1045
01:32:45,313 --> 01:32:48,282
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The GDR gets Abel back
for the Russians...</font></b>

1046
01:32:48,382 --> 01:32:52,286
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">winning their respect and capturing
the headlines for their cause.</font></b>

1047
01:32:52,386 --> 01:32:54,555
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Which, of course, puts East Germany
on the map.</font></b>

1048
01:32:54,655 --> 01:32:57,291
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But we don't care about their map.</font></b>

1049
01:32:57,391 --> 01:32:59,093
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Stick with the Russians.</font></b>

1050
01:32:59,193 --> 01:33:01,273
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Stick with the Russians.
It's Powers for Abel.</font></b>

1051
01:33:01,373 --> 01:33:04,699
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So, does all this mean this
might actually happen?</font></b>

1052
01:33:04,799 --> 01:33:06,601
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah, that's what you
seem to be telling me.</font></b>

1053
01:33:06,901 --> 01:33:09,720
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We'll put Abel on a plane,
he'll be here Friday.</font></b>

1054
01:33:09,820 --> 01:33:11,806
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So, if Schischkin gets the okay,</font></b>

1055
01:33:11,906 --> 01:33:14,108
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">all that's left is the mechanics
of the trade.</font></b>

1056
01:33:14,208 --> 01:33:17,212
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- How we swap our guy for their guy.
- Our "guys".</font></b>

1057
01:33:17,312 --> 01:33:19,814
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Two guys. Powers and Pryor.</font></b>

1058
01:33:20,314 --> 01:33:23,184
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No, now don't go bleeding heart on me.</font></b>

1059
01:33:23,284 --> 01:33:25,820
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Powers is the whole ball game.</font></b>

1060
01:33:25,920 --> 01:33:29,457
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Forget this Ivy League boy, who obviously
thought it was a good idea</font></b>

1061
01:33:29,557 --> 01:33:34,627
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">to study Soviet economics in Berlin
in the middle of the Cold War.</font></b>

1062
01:33:35,629 --> 01:33:38,004
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Powers is who we need.</font></b>

1063
01:33:38,104 --> 01:33:40,469
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You don't even like Powers.</font></b>

1064
01:33:41,168 --> 01:33:43,322
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Everybody hates Powers.</font></b>

1065
01:33:43,422 --> 01:33:48,008
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">He didn't kill himself and he let the commies
parade him on television.</font></b>

1066
01:33:48,108 --> 01:33:50,278
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">He's the most hated man in America.</font></b>

1067
01:33:50,378 --> 01:33:53,303
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">After Rudolf Abel, maybe.</font></b>

1068
01:33:53,403 --> 01:33:55,359
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And me.</font></b>

1069
01:34:03,791 --> 01:34:06,207
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Now wake up!</font></b>

1070
01:34:13,901 --> 01:34:15,703
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I gotta sleep.</font></b>

1071
01:34:15,803 --> 01:34:18,100
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I just gotta sleep.</font></b>

1072
01:34:20,608 --> 01:34:23,978
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I told you, you can sleep once we talk
what we need to talk.</font></b>

1073
01:34:24,078 --> 01:34:26,547
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You must focus on me.</font></b>

1074
01:34:26,647 --> 01:34:30,384
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Your government doesn't care about you.
You know that. Any of you.</font></b>

1075
01:34:30,484 --> 01:34:33,888
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You know that twelve U-2 pilots
incurred brain damage?</font></b>

1076
01:34:33,988 --> 01:34:37,191
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">They're vegetables because of altitude,
insufficient oxygen.</font></b>

1077
01:34:37,391 --> 01:34:41,495
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But they keep you flying, Gary.
You and your friends.</font></b>

1078
01:34:41,595 --> 01:34:45,432
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">They gave you this. A scratcher, yes?</font></b>

1079
01:34:45,532 --> 01:34:47,752
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Potassium cyanide.</font></b>

1080
01:34:48,185 --> 01:34:51,121
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Does that look like they care about you?</font></b>

1081
01:35:20,167 --> 01:35:22,994
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">What is the construction
of the destructor unit?</font></b>

1082
01:35:23,371 --> 01:35:25,439
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">By what means is this unit operated?</font></b>

1083
01:35:25,639 --> 01:35:28,576
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">With what explosives is the unit charged,</font></b>

1084
01:35:28,676 --> 01:35:31,278
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">and what destruction is it capable of?</font></b>

1085
01:35:31,378 --> 01:35:35,456
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I don't know. The pilots were never shown
any of the equipment.</font></b>

1086
01:35:35,556 --> 01:35:38,018
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">How wide far can the radar</font></b>

1087
01:35:38,118 --> 01:35:40,888
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- map an area during an overflight?
- I don't know, I don't know!</font></b>

1088
01:35:40,988 --> 01:35:44,792
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Were you making the overflight
on April 9th</font></b>

1089
01:35:44,892 --> 01:35:48,729
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">over the industrial area and MIG
bomber base at Baranovichi?</font></b>

1090
01:35:48,829 --> 01:35:51,625
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I was not. This was my first overflight.</font></b>

1091
01:35:51,725 --> 01:35:56,036
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I need to know about engine-out
to glide ratio.</font></b>

1092
01:35:56,136 --> 01:35:59,006
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">How the plane gets so high.</font></b>

1093
01:35:59,106 --> 01:36:03,778
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We know it reaches altitude
of 70,000 feet.</font></b>

1094
01:36:04,178 --> 01:36:08,482
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Gary, we know this. And I need to know
where the planes have flown.</font></b>

1095
01:36:08,582 --> 01:36:11,085
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Where they have flown, Gary.</font></b>

1096
01:36:11,185 --> 01:36:13,613
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And we must have this talk now.</font></b>

1097
01:36:16,056 --> 01:36:17,925
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Now.</font></b>

1098
01:36:18,025 --> 01:36:20,690
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And then you can sleep a little.</font></b>

1099
01:36:24,898 --> 01:36:27,308
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Sir, wake up.</font></b>

1100
01:36:28,335 --> 01:36:30,632
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Wake up, sir.</font></b>

1101
01:36:31,806 --> 01:36:33,908
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Sir, can you come with me, please?
- Yeah.</font></b>

1102
01:36:34,008 --> 01:36:35,796
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- We gotta move.
- Yeah, of course.</font></b>

1103
01:36:35,896 --> 01:36:39,680
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Can you come with me, please? Okay.
- Yeah.</font></b>

1104
01:36:39,980 --> 01:36:42,297
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Got your glasses?
- What time is it?</font></b>

1105
01:36:42,397 --> 01:36:44,785
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It's late, but we need to talk...</font></b>

1106
01:36:44,885 --> 01:36:48,321
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">and then we need to get
on a plane, okay?</font></b>

1107
01:36:48,421 --> 01:36:50,723
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Yep. Upsy-daisy!
- Upsy-daisy.</font></b>

1108
01:36:50,823 --> 01:36:55,238
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">That's right. There we go. Keep it moving.
Thank you.</font></b>

1109
01:36:56,931 --> 01:36:59,733
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Other way, other way. There we go.</font></b>

1110
01:36:59,833 --> 01:37:02,703
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- You say a plane?
- This way, please. Keep moving.</font></b>

1111
01:37:02,803 --> 01:37:05,675
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So, I received a favorable decision</font></b>

1112
01:37:05,775 --> 01:37:07,908
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">from Moscow on your proposal</font></b>

1113
01:37:08,008 --> 01:37:11,145
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">that we help our friends in the German
Democratic Republic...</font></b>

1114
01:37:11,545 --> 01:37:16,199
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">by exchanging Mr. Powers for Mr. Abel.</font></b>

1115
01:37:17,117 --> 01:37:18,385
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">That's swell.</font></b>

1116
01:37:18,485 --> 01:37:22,690
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">May I suggest the Glienicke Bridge
as a place of a swap?</font></b>

1117
01:37:22,790 --> 01:37:26,694
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Why not Checkpoint Charlie?
- We're not looking for publicity.</font></b>

1118
01:37:26,794 --> 01:37:30,164
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The Glienicke Bridge is very quiet,
especially early in the morning.</font></b>

1119
01:37:30,264 --> 01:37:32,867
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Glienicke Bridge. I'll run that by our side.</font></b>

1120
01:37:32,967 --> 01:37:36,603
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We can have Abel here on Friday.
So, Saturday morning?</font></b>

1121
01:37:36,703 --> 01:37:39,840
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Always impatience, yeah?
- I want to get home and get into bed.</font></b>

1122
01:37:39,940 --> 01:37:42,142
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So, Saturday morning?</font></b>

1123
01:37:42,242 --> 01:37:45,412
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- 5:30?
- Alright.</font></b>

1124
01:37:45,512 --> 01:37:48,415
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We're done here. This
is a number...</font></b>

1125
01:37:48,515 --> 01:37:51,785
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">in case anything
should come up.</font></b>

1126
01:37:51,885 --> 01:37:55,656
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Alright.
- Someone will answer at any hour.</font></b>

1127
01:37:55,956 --> 01:37:58,453
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I don't expect to use it.</font></b>

1128
01:37:58,959 --> 01:38:01,495
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Shall we toast the arrangement?</font></b>

1129
01:38:01,917 --> 01:38:03,826
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Why not?</font></b>

1130
01:38:04,531 --> 01:38:06,853
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Armenian brandy. Good bracer
for your cold.</font></b>

1131
01:38:06,953 --> 01:38:08,839
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Thank you.</font></b>

1132
01:38:08,939 --> 01:38:10,170
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Would you mind...</font></b>

1133
01:38:10,270 --> 01:38:12,917
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">This is not part of our
business but...</font></b>

1134
01:38:13,017 --> 01:38:15,743
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'd like to ask you a couple of questions.
You do not have to answer.</font></b>

1135
01:38:15,843 --> 01:38:18,245
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I shall answer what I know.</font></b>

1136
01:38:18,345 --> 01:38:21,315
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I like this guy, your guy.</font></b>

1137
01:38:21,415 --> 01:38:24,251
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">What happens to your guy
when he gets home?</font></b>

1138
01:38:24,351 --> 01:38:28,989
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, we have to make a determination
whether our guy is now your guy.</font></b>

1139
01:38:29,089 --> 01:38:33,627
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Now, as I said to you before, he's acted honorably.
He's still your guy, believe me.</font></b>

1140
01:38:33,727 --> 01:38:36,830
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Of course you will say that
if it were true...</font></b>

1141
01:38:36,930 --> 01:38:39,066
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">and if it were not true.</font></b>

1142
01:38:39,166 --> 01:38:41,468
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I guess it has come down to that?</font></b>

1143
01:38:41,568 --> 01:38:44,394
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, forgive me for pushing, but...</font></b>

1144
01:38:44,494 --> 01:38:48,308
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">is he in any danger if the determination is made?</font></b>

1145
01:38:48,408 --> 01:38:50,678
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, goodness.</font></b>

1146
01:38:50,778 --> 01:38:53,580
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">As things are now, everyone is in danger.</font></b>

1147
01:38:53,680 --> 01:38:56,656
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Cheers.
- Na zdorovie.</font></b>

1148
01:39:08,996 --> 01:39:12,132
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">There will be no exchange
on Glienicke Bridge.</font></b>

1149
01:39:12,232 --> 01:39:14,101
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Excuse me, sir.</font></b>

1150
01:39:14,201 --> 01:39:17,104
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">There will be no exchange.</font></b>

1151
01:39:17,204 --> 01:39:18,706
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Not for Frederic Pryor.</font></b>

1152
01:39:18,806 --> 01:39:21,792
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Mr. Vogel, I thought yesterday
we had agreed.</font></b>

1153
01:39:21,892 --> 01:39:24,674
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We agreed on an exchange,
Abel for Pryor.</font></b>

1154
01:39:26,113 --> 01:39:29,183
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Now I learn you are a rug merchant</font></b>

1155
01:39:29,283 --> 01:39:32,086
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">selling the same rug to two customers.</font></b>

1156
01:39:32,186 --> 01:39:34,788
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Abel for Pryor you sell to us.
- Yeah.</font></b>

1157
01:39:34,888 --> 01:39:37,224
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And Abel for Powers you sell
to the Soviets.</font></b>

1158
01:39:37,324 --> 01:39:39,690
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'm not quite sure what the problem is</font></b>

1159
01:39:39,790 --> 01:39:43,221
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">if the arrangement satisfies two parties
or three or four.</font></b>

1160
01:39:43,321 --> 01:39:47,227
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- What difference does it make?
- The arrangement does not satisfy this party.</font></b>

1161
01:39:51,238 --> 01:39:52,419
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Now, Mr. Vogel,
please...</font></b>

1162
01:39:52,519 --> 01:39:56,038
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Obviously you do not know
who you are dealing with.</font></b>

1163
01:39:57,261 --> 01:40:00,749
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Here's the interest of the German
Democratic Republic.</font></b>

1164
01:40:01,248 --> 01:40:05,285
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">To deal with, and to be seen to be dealing
with another sovereign power,</font></b>

1165
01:40:05,385 --> 01:40:09,056
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">the United States. An equal power.</font></b>

1166
01:40:09,156 --> 01:40:12,359
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Instead you treat us as stooges for the
Union of Soviet Socialist Republics.</font></b>

1167
01:40:12,459 --> 01:40:15,721
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Can we just call them the Russians?
It'll save time.</font></b>

1168
01:40:16,630 --> 01:40:19,734
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I have an appointment, sir. I think
it's you who are wasting time.</font></b>

1169
01:40:19,834 --> 01:40:23,721
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Now, tell me if I am describing this wrong.
You have a kid, a university student.</font></b>

1170
01:40:23,871 --> 01:40:26,674
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Someone you know is not a spy,
who's no threat to you.</font></b>

1171
01:40:26,774 --> 01:40:29,910
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And in exchange for this person
who is worthless to you,</font></b>

1172
01:40:30,110 --> 01:40:34,314
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">you play an equal part in an exchange between
the Russians and the Americans.</font></b>

1173
01:40:34,414 --> 01:40:38,752
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And this is one transaction between us
and the two of you.</font></b>

1174
01:40:38,852 --> 01:40:42,356
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We're not trying to do two things here, sir.
We're just doing one thing. One, one, one.</font></b>

1175
01:40:42,456 --> 01:40:47,161
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It's hard for me to see how the Republic of
East German Democrats is being slighted.</font></b>

1176
01:40:47,261 --> 01:40:50,164
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You agreed with the Soviets
without consulting me.</font></b>

1177
01:40:50,264 --> 01:40:53,035
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Is this a negotiation or a conspiracy?
- For it to be a conspiracy,</font></b>

1178
01:40:53,135 --> 01:40:55,628
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">there would have to be harm to you.
There's just benefits here.</font></b>

1179
01:40:55,728 --> 01:40:59,674
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- We're of agreeing interests.
- No, you decide they agree.</font></b>

1180
01:41:00,274 --> 01:41:03,477
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Where is your appointment, sir?
- In the West. Ku'damm.</font></b>

1181
01:41:03,577 --> 01:41:05,307
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Good.</font></b>

1182
01:41:15,722 --> 01:41:20,001
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Look around you. How does the Eastern sector
compare with the West?</font></b>

1183
01:41:22,262 --> 01:41:26,666
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Our Russian friends have decided that
we should not rebuild our capital city.</font></b>

1184
01:41:28,468 --> 01:41:31,745
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But we live in this ruin made
by our Russian friends.</font></b>

1185
01:41:31,845 --> 01:41:35,305
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Go ahead, make your deal with these Russians.
We won't be part of it.</font></b>

1186
01:41:37,477 --> 01:41:39,813
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">There is no deal without Pryor.
We're not leaving him here.</font></b>

1187
01:41:39,913 --> 01:41:45,302
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Is this your position or your government's?
- Sir, I'm here. I'm talking to you.</font></b>

1188
01:41:45,402 --> 01:41:48,599
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But you are not a representative of your government.
You don't know who you are.</font></b>

1189
01:41:48,699 --> 01:41:52,755
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Neither do we. You should be careful.
This is not Brooklyn, Mr. Donovan.</font></b>

1190
01:42:00,333 --> 01:42:03,437
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Look, sir. You must know that
in every respect that matters,</font></b>

1191
01:42:03,537 --> 01:42:07,125
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I represent my government.
You know who I am.</font></b>

1192
01:42:08,225 --> 01:42:09,208
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Do I?</font></b>

1193
01:42:31,498 --> 01:42:33,767
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Do you have the proper papers?</font></b>

1194
01:42:33,867 --> 01:42:36,870
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Of course not. It doesn't matter.</font></b>

1195
01:42:36,970 --> 01:42:40,073
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">An American lawyer like you can
talk your way out of anything.</font></b>

1196
01:42:40,173 --> 01:42:42,171
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Can't you?</font></b>

1197
01:43:24,184 --> 01:43:26,845
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- You go with him.
- Why?</font></b>

1198
01:43:26,945 --> 01:43:30,190
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- It's passport problem.
- What problem? What's the problem?</font></b>

1199
01:43:30,290 --> 01:43:32,487
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You go with him.</font></b>

1200
01:43:34,394 --> 01:43:38,719
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And remember, we control
the fate of Frederic Pryor.</font></b>

1201
01:45:22,402 --> 01:45:24,479
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">My God!</font></b>

1202
01:45:58,972 --> 01:46:01,341
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah, I'll start with some coffee, please.</font></b>

1203
01:46:01,441 --> 01:46:05,412
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Then I'll have the Hilton combo
and the American breakfast.</font></b>

1204
01:46:05,512 --> 01:46:08,047
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- And coffee.
- Both breakfasts?</font></b>

1205
01:46:08,147 --> 01:46:10,350
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Yeah, yeah.
- One first or...</font></b>

1206
01:46:10,450 --> 01:46:14,758
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Both first, both. Whenever they're ready.
And coffee.</font></b>

1207
01:46:32,038 --> 01:46:33,740
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You shouldn't be here.</font></b>

1208
01:46:33,840 --> 01:46:37,757
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, sometimes in Germany, you just
want a big American breakfast.</font></b>

1209
01:46:40,980 --> 01:46:43,049
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">What happened? Where were you last night?</font></b>

1210
01:46:43,149 --> 01:46:46,152
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Vogel arranged for me to spend
some time in the East.</font></b>

1211
01:46:46,252 --> 01:46:47,254
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Oh, Jesus.</font></b>

1212
01:46:47,354 --> 01:46:51,553
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Frankly, it's not that much worse than
where you have me here in the West.</font></b>

1213
01:46:52,726 --> 01:46:55,929
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">So the Russians are fine
with the exchange,</font></b>

1214
01:46:56,029 --> 01:46:58,965
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">but now Vogel is saying that
the East Germans won't do it.</font></b>

1215
01:46:59,065 --> 01:47:01,168
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We're not gonna get Pryor.</font></b>

1216
01:47:01,268 --> 01:47:05,335
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Great, good. So the Soviets are set.
We get Powers.</font></b>

1217
01:47:05,435 --> 01:47:08,775
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We get Powers. Well done.</font></b>

1218
01:47:08,875 --> 01:47:10,844
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No, the East Germans won't do it.</font></b>

1219
01:47:10,944 --> 01:47:14,714
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We won't get Pryor, and that kid matters.
Every person matters.</font></b>

1220
01:47:14,814 --> 01:47:17,634
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Sure, that's why you tried.
That's why you tried.</font></b>

1221
01:47:17,734 --> 01:47:20,153
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Abel's on his way, so we're all set
for tomorrow morning.</font></b>

1222
01:47:20,253 --> 01:47:22,255
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Makes things simple.
Makes things simple.</font></b>

1223
01:47:22,355 --> 01:47:24,458
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We are not getting the kid.</font></b>

1224
01:47:24,658 --> 01:47:26,926
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah, I understand. We're set.</font></b>

1225
01:47:27,026 --> 01:47:29,758
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We can ignore the message
we got this morning.</font></b>

1226
01:47:30,430 --> 01:47:31,698
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">What message?</font></b>

1227
01:47:31,798 --> 01:47:34,834
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">From the East Germans. They
called the number I gave you.</font></b>

1228
01:47:34,934 --> 01:47:37,170
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">They said they wanted
to speak to you today.</font></b>

1229
01:47:37,270 --> 01:47:40,753
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Vogel called?
- No. Office...</font></b>

1230
01:47:40,853 --> 01:47:43,193
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Harald Ott, East German attorney general.</font></b>

1231
01:47:43,293 --> 01:47:44,944
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Wanting what? What does he want?</font></b>

1232
01:47:45,044 --> 01:47:48,715
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, to talk to you. But it's okay,
I can't ask you to go back there.</font></b>

1233
01:47:48,815 --> 01:47:51,551
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And listen, you seem to be persona non grata
to some elements,</font></b>

1234
01:47:51,651 --> 01:47:55,021
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- so we won't push our luck.
- So he wants to see me.</font></b>

1235
01:47:55,121 --> 01:47:56,990
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">What time?</font></b>

1236
01:47:57,090 --> 01:47:59,959
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Oh, no, no. Now, listen. You...</font></b>

1237
01:48:00,059 --> 01:48:03,997
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You don't need to go. In fact, you shouldn't go.
In fact, you can't go.</font></b>

1238
01:48:04,297 --> 01:48:06,666
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We're set with the Soviets. We
don't want to screw it up.</font></b>

1239
01:48:06,766 --> 01:48:08,835
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- I'm not gonna screw it up.
- You're not going!</font></b>

1240
01:48:08,935 --> 01:48:11,738
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Don't be a pain in the ass.
- I ordered.</font></b>

1241
01:48:11,838 --> 01:48:14,403
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Enjoy your big American breakfast.</font></b>

1242
01:48:23,450 --> 01:48:27,754
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I thought it should be negotiated at the highest level
as a courtesy to you.</font></b>

1243
01:48:27,854 --> 01:48:30,252
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I thank you, sir.</font></b>

1244
01:48:31,891 --> 01:48:34,874
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I don't know how things
became so confused.</font></b>

1245
01:48:34,974 --> 01:48:38,510
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, I guess sometimes they just do.</font></b>

1246
01:48:42,068 --> 01:48:46,172
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">For sake of clarity, I say we are
fully prepared to exchange</font></b>

1247
01:48:46,272 --> 01:48:50,510
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">the so-called student, Pryor,
for Rudolf Abel.</font></b>

1248
01:48:50,610 --> 01:48:53,680
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I understand from Mr. Vogel that
Pryor is very important to you.</font></b>

1249
01:48:53,780 --> 01:48:55,081
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yes, but...</font></b>

1250
01:48:55,181 --> 01:48:58,546
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We'll do a memorandum to that effect.</font></b>

1251
01:48:59,118 --> 01:49:00,887
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Oh, a memorandum.</font></b>

1252
01:49:00,987 --> 01:49:05,453
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Certainly, we commit to
a bi-lateral exchange.</font></b>

1253
01:49:05,892 --> 01:49:10,263
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yes, yes, sure. I'm not sure
what that means but...</font></b>

1254
01:49:10,363 --> 01:49:14,968
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">My country also insists on
Francis Gary Powers.</font></b>

1255
01:49:15,068 --> 01:49:16,431
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No!</font></b>

1256
01:49:21,207 --> 01:49:24,711
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">This is how things became so confused.</font></b>

1257
01:49:24,811 --> 01:49:27,280
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Powers. What use is he, sir?</font></b>

1258
01:49:27,380 --> 01:49:30,550
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You want him back for punitive reasons?
What's done is done.</font></b>

1259
01:49:30,650 --> 01:49:34,721
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">He has divulged what he will divulge,
as no doubt Abel has also.</font></b>

1260
01:49:34,821 --> 01:49:39,726
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We are offering instead someone
who you insist is innocent.</font></b>

1261
01:49:39,826 --> 01:49:43,329
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And this is right. This is who
you should retrieve.</font></b>

1262
01:49:43,429 --> 01:49:46,828
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The future. Look to the future.</font></b>

1263
01:49:49,586 --> 01:49:51,163
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Ott.</font></b>

1264
01:49:53,740 --> 01:49:55,463
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Ott.</font></b>

1265
01:50:04,017 --> 01:50:07,115
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'm sorry. If you could
give me a moment, sir.</font></b>

1266
01:50:26,105 --> 01:50:30,777
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'm very sorry. The attorney general regrets
that he had to leave on urgent business.</font></b>

1267
01:50:30,877 --> 01:50:34,147
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- He left?
- Yes. Many apologies.</font></b>

1268
01:50:34,247 --> 01:50:38,181
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- I've been waiting for over an hour.
- Very sorry, sir.</font></b>

1269
01:50:40,353 --> 01:50:42,409
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Young man.</font></b>

1270
01:50:43,790 --> 01:50:45,887
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Come here.</font></b>

1271
01:50:46,462 --> 01:50:48,856
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It's alright. Come here.</font></b>

1272
01:50:55,048 --> 01:50:57,165
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Take a seat.</font></b>

1273
01:50:57,737 --> 01:51:01,102
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Oh, come on, come on. Sit down.</font></b>

1274
01:51:04,177 --> 01:51:06,391
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Do you like your job here?</font></b>

1275
01:51:06,779 --> 01:51:10,216
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- It's a very good job, sir.
- It must be. Must be interesting.</font></b>

1276
01:51:10,316 --> 01:51:13,620
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Oh, yes, sir.
- And important, too.</font></b>

1277
01:51:13,720 --> 01:51:16,123
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And your English is...is good.</font></b>

1278
01:51:16,623 --> 01:51:19,609
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yes, I hesitate to say it's excellent.
But it's excellent, sir.</font></b>

1279
01:51:19,709 --> 01:51:21,578
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Good, good. Good.</font></b>

1280
01:51:21,678 --> 01:51:26,433
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">See, I just lost my negotiating partner
and I need somebody to talk to,</font></b>

1281
01:51:26,533 --> 01:51:28,864
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">and you seem like a reasonable young man.</font></b>

1282
01:51:30,169 --> 01:51:32,600
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Can I talk to you?</font></b>

1283
01:51:34,874 --> 01:51:36,742
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It's alright.</font></b>

1284
01:51:36,856 --> 01:51:39,407
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It's alright. I just...</font></b>

1285
01:51:39,913 --> 01:51:42,985
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I just need you to give a message
to your boss.</font></b>

1286
01:51:44,451 --> 01:51:47,487
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But it has to be very, very, very clear.</font></b>

1287
01:51:47,587 --> 01:51:48,676
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You understand?</font></b>

1288
01:51:49,923 --> 01:51:52,892
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yes, sir. But perhaps you
should wait until he...</font></b>

1289
01:51:52,992 --> 01:51:56,826
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No, no. The thing is, I have this cold
and I wanna get home...</font></b>

1290
01:51:57,096 --> 01:51:59,468
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">and get in bed.</font></b>

1291
01:52:00,833 --> 01:52:04,266
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Can you give him the message?
- Certainly.</font></b>

1292
01:52:05,572 --> 01:52:07,636
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, this is the message.</font></b>

1293
01:52:08,808 --> 01:52:12,774
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">"There is no deal for Abel unless
we get Powers and Pryor."</font></b>

1294
01:52:13,312 --> 01:52:15,315
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Do you understand?
- Yes, sir.</font></b>

1295
01:52:15,415 --> 01:52:19,485
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It's arranged for tomorrow morning. It
will not happen unless we get two men.</font></b>

1296
01:52:19,585 --> 01:52:22,939
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Those two men. Two, two, two.
- Yes, sir.</font></b>

1297
01:52:23,389 --> 01:52:25,892
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">If there is no deal...</font></b>

1298
01:52:25,992 --> 01:52:28,595
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">your boss must tell the Soviets.</font></b>

1299
01:52:29,362 --> 01:52:34,286
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">He has to tell the Soviets that they
are not getting Rudolf Abel.</font></b>

1300
01:52:35,568 --> 01:52:37,814
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yes, sir.</font></b>

1301
01:52:40,006 --> 01:52:42,362
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Oh, and tell him this.</font></b>

1302
01:52:42,742 --> 01:52:45,745
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">That so far, Abel has been a good soldier,</font></b>

1303
01:52:45,845 --> 01:52:48,388
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">but he thinks he's going home.</font></b>

1304
01:52:50,316 --> 01:52:52,552
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">If we had to tell him that
he's not going home,</font></b>

1305
01:52:52,652 --> 01:52:55,488
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">that the Soviets don't even want him,
that he's never going home...</font></b>

1306
01:52:55,588 --> 01:52:59,020
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, I imagine his behavior might change.</font></b>

1307
01:52:59,793 --> 01:53:03,476
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And who will be held responsible for that?</font></b>

1308
01:53:06,533 --> 01:53:08,914
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">That's a long message.</font></b>

1309
01:53:09,014 --> 01:53:11,665
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Did you get it all?
- Yes, sir. Got it.</font></b>

1310
01:53:11,765 --> 01:53:13,773
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Good.</font></b>

1311
01:53:13,873 --> 01:53:15,375
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You're a good man.</font></b>

1312
01:53:17,977 --> 01:53:22,515
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">And also tell him there's no deal unless we
hear before the end of business today.</font></b>

1313
01:53:22,615 --> 01:53:24,017
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">He has the number.</font></b>

1314
01:53:24,117 --> 01:53:26,052
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">If the exchange isn't gonna happen,</font></b>

1315
01:53:26,152 --> 01:53:28,933
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">no reason for everybody to get up
first thing in the morning.</font></b>

1316
01:53:29,033 --> 01:53:31,458
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">No, sir, that would be pointless.</font></b>

1317
01:53:31,858 --> 01:53:33,828
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You're kidding me!</font></b>

1318
01:53:33,928 --> 01:53:36,796
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- You're kidding me!
- Not really. I need some change.</font></b>

1319
01:53:36,896 --> 01:53:39,365
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">This is exactly what you
weren't supposed to do.</font></b>

1320
01:53:39,465 --> 01:53:42,001
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">My instructions were to
feel out the situation.</font></b>

1321
01:53:42,101 --> 01:53:44,637
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Your instructions were to get Powers,
not Pryor.</font></b>

1322
01:53:44,737 --> 01:53:47,006
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">That was not the original deal.
You fouled it all up!</font></b>

1323
01:53:47,106 --> 01:53:49,876
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">How do you know? I feel
pretty good about it.</font></b>

1324
01:53:49,976 --> 01:53:53,112
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- You fucked it all up!
- Oh, don't worry.</font></b>

1325
01:53:53,212 --> 01:53:58,279
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- I think it's gonna be fine.
- How do you know? You don't know that.</font></b>

1326
01:54:01,020 --> 01:54:05,180
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">United States. New York, New York. Danke.</font></b>

1327
01:54:05,858 --> 01:54:08,361
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Look, this whole thing...</font></b>

1328
01:54:08,861 --> 01:54:11,137
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">has been to feel me out.</font></b>

1329
01:54:11,498 --> 01:54:15,168
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Would I swap one for one and which one?</font></b>

1330
01:54:15,268 --> 01:54:18,738
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But I said "no, two for one". So they know
where we stand.</font></b>

1331
01:54:18,938 --> 01:54:20,907
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah, what if they think
about it and say...</font></b>

1332
01:54:21,007 --> 01:54:24,538
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">"Forget it! You keep our guy,
we keep your guys"?</font></b>

1333
01:54:26,179 --> 01:54:28,714
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, then I have fucked it all up.</font></b>

1334
01:54:28,814 --> 01:54:30,950
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Hey, honey! It's me.</font></b>

1335
01:54:31,050 --> 01:54:34,635
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah. The fishing's been great.</font></b>

1336
01:54:35,622 --> 01:54:40,109
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'm in London, just for one more meeting,
then I'm on my way home.</font></b>

1337
01:54:40,526 --> 01:54:43,730
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah, yeah, I remember that marmalade.</font></b>

1338
01:54:43,830 --> 01:54:46,912
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It's that shop right by Regent's Park.</font></b>

1339
01:54:47,433 --> 01:54:51,805
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Alright, I will if I have the time.
Hey, can I say hi to Roger?</font></b>

1340
01:54:52,405 --> 01:54:54,707
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Could I say hi to the girls?</font></b>

1341
01:54:54,807 --> 01:54:57,276
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Is anyone not busy?</font></b>

1342
01:54:57,376 --> 01:55:00,581
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Have they even noticed I'm not around?</font></b>

1343
01:55:56,068 --> 01:55:58,304
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We're on.</font></b>

1344
01:55:58,404 --> 01:55:59,973
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Two for one.</font></b>

1345
01:56:00,673 --> 01:56:02,207
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Hot dog.</font></b>

1346
01:56:02,975 --> 01:56:04,944
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Let's have a drink.</font></b>

1347
01:56:05,044 --> 01:56:07,714
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- One wrinkle.
- What is that?</font></b>

1348
01:56:07,814 --> 01:56:10,416
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">They won't release Pryor with Powers,
not at the bridge.</font></b>

1349
01:56:10,516 --> 01:56:12,045
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">They'll release him at the same time.</font></b>

1350
01:56:12,145 --> 01:56:14,320
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">When the Russians give us Powers
on the bridge,</font></b>

1351
01:56:14,420 --> 01:56:16,789
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">they'll release Pryor over
Checkpoint Charlie.</font></b>

1352
01:56:16,889 --> 01:56:18,724
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">What does that mean?</font></b>

1353
01:56:18,824 --> 01:56:22,529
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I think it means, "we wanna
have the last word".</font></b>

1354
01:56:22,729 --> 01:56:24,831
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But they will do it.</font></b>

1355
01:56:24,931 --> 01:56:27,008
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You tell me. You felt them out.</font></b>

1356
01:56:47,620 --> 01:56:50,423
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Where are they? Where's our guy?
Where's our guy?</font></b>

1357
01:56:50,523 --> 01:56:53,926
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- They're late.
- Nobody's late. We're early.</font></b>

1358
01:56:54,026 --> 01:56:56,757
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- May I?
- Yeah.</font></b>

1359
01:57:02,635 --> 01:57:04,704
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Hoffman.
- Yeah?</font></b>

1360
01:57:04,804 --> 01:57:08,241
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- I think they have...
- What?</font></b>

1361
01:57:08,341 --> 01:57:12,411
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Snipers.
- Well, I'm sure they do.</font></b>

1362
01:57:12,511 --> 01:57:14,680
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">How are you sure they do?</font></b>

1363
01:57:14,780 --> 01:57:17,378
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Because we have snipers.</font></b>

1364
01:57:34,200 --> 01:57:36,430
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Step out, sir.</font></b>

1365
01:57:43,909 --> 01:57:45,940
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Jim.</font></b>

1366
01:57:49,382 --> 01:57:51,645
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Dear Jim.</font></b>

1367
01:57:53,719 --> 01:57:56,590
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- How are you?
- Happy to see you.</font></b>

1368
01:57:57,090 --> 01:57:58,958
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Have you arranged all this for me?</font></b>

1369
01:57:59,058 --> 01:58:03,162
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, let's see what this is before
I...I take credit for it.</font></b>

1370
01:58:03,262 --> 01:58:06,304
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Any word about Pryor from
Checkpoint Charlie?</font></b>

1371
01:58:29,705 --> 01:58:31,659
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Nothing cooking yet.</font></b>

1372
01:58:37,797 --> 01:58:39,232
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Excuse me, sir.</font></b>

1373
01:58:39,332 --> 01:58:43,403
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">This is Lieutenant Joe Murphy, United States Air Force,
here to identify Powers.</font></b>

1374
01:58:44,303 --> 01:58:47,602
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Lieutenant Murphy.
- Sir.</font></b>

1375
01:58:50,176 --> 01:58:54,080
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">There may be a slight glitch. I
was a young man when I left.</font></b>

1376
01:58:54,180 --> 01:58:57,036
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Who will they find to identify me?</font></b>

1377
01:58:57,550 --> 01:59:00,119
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, I hope it's not your
East German family.</font></b>

1378
01:59:00,219 --> 01:59:03,072
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I doubt they could identify each other.</font></b>

1379
01:59:37,323 --> 01:59:39,646
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Looks like our party.</font></b>

1380
01:59:46,465 --> 01:59:50,804
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Well, let's go. You can
stay here, Donovan.</font></b>

1381
01:59:51,604 --> 01:59:53,618
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Not likely.</font></b>

1382
01:59:55,257 --> 01:59:57,463
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Open the gate.</font></b>

1383
02:00:11,224 --> 02:00:14,060
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">What do you think will happen
when you get home?</font></b>

1384
02:00:14,160 --> 02:00:16,495
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I think...</font></b>

1385
02:00:16,595 --> 02:00:19,040
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'll have a vodka.</font></b>

1386
02:00:21,267 --> 02:00:23,135
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah.</font></b>

1387
02:00:23,235 --> 02:00:24,537
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah.</font></b>

1388
02:00:24,637 --> 02:00:27,173
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But, Rudolf, is there not
the possibility...</font></b>

1389
02:00:27,273 --> 02:00:30,343
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">That my people are going to shoot me?</font></b>

1390
02:00:30,743 --> 02:00:32,473
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yes.</font></b>

1391
02:00:33,579 --> 02:00:36,568
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- You're not worried?
- Would it help?</font></b>

1392
02:00:47,793 --> 02:00:50,696
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">To answer your question, my friend,</font></b>

1393
02:00:50,796 --> 02:00:54,161
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I acted honorably. I think they know that.</font></b>

1394
02:00:54,667 --> 02:00:58,666
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">But sometimes people think wrong.
People are people.</font></b>

1395
02:00:59,505 --> 02:01:02,035
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Let's see how they greet me.</font></b>

1396
02:01:02,708 --> 02:01:05,026
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">What can I look for?</font></b>

1397
02:01:07,213 --> 02:01:11,780
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">If I'm embraced or just shown
the back seat.</font></b>

1398
02:01:51,457 --> 02:01:53,187
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Da.</font></b>

1399
02:02:05,404 --> 02:02:07,709
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Take off the hat.</font></b>

1400
02:02:13,295 --> 02:02:14,939
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Hey, Powers.</font></b>

1401
02:02:16,398 --> 02:02:18,527
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Hey, Murph.</font></b>

1402
02:02:19,485 --> 02:02:21,915
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah, that's Powers.</font></b>

1403
02:02:23,356 --> 02:02:25,891
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Alright, Mr. Donovan.
We go now!</font></b>

1404
02:02:26,191 --> 02:02:28,395
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Hang on.</font></b>

1405
02:02:34,433 --> 02:02:37,078
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Believe me, I will tell you.</font></b>

1406
02:02:38,003 --> 02:02:39,527
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">There's no one here.</font></b>

1407
02:02:42,675 --> 02:02:44,777
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">They're releasing another man
at Checkpoint Charlie.</font></b>

1408
02:02:44,877 --> 02:02:47,012
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We're just confirming that he's there.</font></b>

1409
02:02:47,112 --> 02:02:48,447
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Now!</font></b>

1410
02:02:48,547 --> 02:02:50,844
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">As per plan, if you please.</font></b>

1411
02:02:52,150 --> 02:02:55,688
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Let's go. Pryor will show up
or he won't. Let's go.</font></b>

1412
02:02:55,788 --> 02:02:58,291
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">They're waiting to see if
we'll do it without him.</font></b>

1413
02:02:58,491 --> 02:03:01,789
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We just have to stand here,
show them we won't.</font></b>

1414
02:03:02,194 --> 02:03:05,322
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I don't give a shit what they want.
We have our objective.</font></b>

1415
02:03:05,422 --> 02:03:07,616
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Go ahead, Abel.</font></b>

1416
02:03:07,716 --> 02:03:10,119
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Go ahead, sir. You can go.</font></b>

1417
02:03:10,469 --> 02:03:15,035
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">If it is not to plan, we go home. We
exchange now or we go home!</font></b>

1418
02:03:17,209 --> 02:03:20,679
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- You're waiting for another man?
- Yup.</font></b>

1419
02:03:20,779 --> 02:03:23,239
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You want him, too.</font></b>

1420
02:03:24,450 --> 02:03:25,438
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I want him.</font></b>

1421
02:03:25,538 --> 02:03:29,455
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Doesn't matter what he wants, sir. I'm
in charge and you are free to go.</font></b>

1422
02:03:29,555 --> 02:03:32,468
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Please go. Walk across.</font></b>

1423
02:03:43,068 --> 02:03:45,275
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I can wait.</font></b>

1424
02:04:09,361 --> 02:04:12,708
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It's something. I'm not sure yet.</font></b>

1425
02:04:14,299 --> 02:04:16,364
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Hang on!</font></b>

1426
02:05:00,012 --> 02:05:01,909
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Let's go.</font></b>

1427
02:05:07,586 --> 02:05:09,523
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">We got him!</font></b>

1428
02:05:10,482 --> 02:05:12,305
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I...</font></b>

1429
02:05:13,692 --> 02:05:16,328
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I sent you a gift, Jim.</font></b>

1430
02:05:16,428 --> 02:05:19,292
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It's a...it's a painting.</font></b>

1431
02:05:19,632 --> 02:05:22,310
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I hope it has some meaning to you.</font></b>

1432
02:05:24,152 --> 02:05:27,130
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I'm sorry. I didn't think
to get you a gift.</font></b>

1433
02:05:29,892 --> 02:05:32,258
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">This is your gift.</font></b>

1434
02:05:35,047 --> 02:05:37,078
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">This is your gift.</font></b>

1435
02:06:11,884 --> 02:06:13,914
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You okay?</font></b>

1436
02:06:14,420 --> 02:06:16,828
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Let's go, let's go, let's go!</font></b>

1437
02:07:35,801 --> 02:07:40,272
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Mr. Donovan. Colonel Abel asked me
to give this to you.</font></b>

1438
02:07:42,674 --> 02:07:44,905
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Pardon me, sir.</font></b>

1439
02:07:45,644 --> 02:07:48,094
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Were you in charge of this thing, sir?</font></b>

1440
02:07:48,414 --> 02:07:51,628
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Yeah.
- Well, I gotta thank you.</font></b>

1441
02:07:51,728 --> 02:07:54,181
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I gotta thank somebody.</font></b>

1442
02:08:10,302 --> 02:08:14,173
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I gave them nothing. I gave them nothing.</font></b>

1443
02:08:14,273 --> 02:08:16,074
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It doesn't matter.</font></b>

1444
02:08:16,174 --> 02:08:18,410
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">It doesn't matter what people think.</font></b>

1445
02:08:18,510 --> 02:08:20,792
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You know what you did.</font></b>

1446
02:09:10,796 --> 02:09:13,102
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Welcome home.</font></b>

1447
02:09:14,299 --> 02:09:16,563
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">What a trip.</font></b>

1448
02:09:27,512 --> 02:09:29,547
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">You okay?</font></b>

1449
02:09:29,647 --> 02:09:32,112
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yeah, I'm fine.</font></b>

1450
02:09:32,751 --> 02:09:36,162
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Did you get the marmalade?
- Yes, yes. Yep.</font></b>

1451
02:09:36,262 --> 02:09:37,789
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Yep.</font></b>

1452
02:09:37,889 --> 02:09:39,753
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I did.</font></b>

1453
02:09:40,659 --> 02:09:42,087
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">As ordered.</font></b>

1454
02:09:46,581 --> 02:09:48,233
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Jim.</font></b>

1455
02:09:48,333 --> 02:09:50,335
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- This is from Arno's.
- So?</font></b>

1456
02:09:50,435 --> 02:09:52,860
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- On the corner!
- Well, honey, I was busy. I'm sorry.</font></b>

1457
02:09:52,960 --> 02:09:55,626
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Oh, for Pete's sake.
- We were so busy. How's Roger? Is he home?</font></b>

1458
02:09:55,726 --> 02:09:58,610
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">He's home. Carol's home, Peggy's home.
Everyone's home.</font></b>

1459
02:09:58,710 --> 02:10:01,914
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Mom! Come quick! Look!</font></b>

1460
02:10:02,414 --> 02:10:03,982
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Mom, come here!</font></b>

1461
02:10:04,082 --> 02:10:06,852
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">- Come see this! Look! Watch!
- Come on!</font></b>

1462
02:10:06,952 --> 02:10:08,987
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Francis Gary Powers</font></b>

1463
02:10:09,087 --> 02:10:13,058
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">has been released from prison
in the Soviet Union</font></b>

1464
02:10:13,158 --> 02:10:17,803
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">and turned over to American authorities
early this morning in Berlin.</font></b>

1465
02:10:17,963 --> 02:10:22,768
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">The President has commuted
the sentence of Rudolf Abel.</font></b>

1466
02:10:22,868 --> 02:10:25,571
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Mr. Abel has been deported</font></b>

1467
02:10:25,671 --> 02:10:28,112
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">and has been released in Berlin.</font></b>

1468
02:10:28,440 --> 02:10:31,777
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Efforts to obtain Mr. Powers' release</font></b>

1469
02:10:31,877 --> 02:10:34,613
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">had been underway for some time.</font></b>

1470
02:10:34,713 --> 02:10:38,054
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">In recent efforts, the United States government</font></b>

1471
02:10:38,154 --> 02:10:42,721
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">has had the cooperation and assistance
of Mr. James B. Donovan,</font></b>

1472
02:10:42,821 --> 02:10:45,057
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">a New York attorney.</font></b>

1473
02:10:45,157 --> 02:10:48,894
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Frederic L. Pryor, an American student</font></b>

1474
02:10:48,994 --> 02:10:51,557
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">held by East German authorities</font></b>

1475
02:10:51,657 --> 02:10:54,082
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">since August of 1961...</font></b>

1476
02:10:54,232 --> 02:10:56,301
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">I thought Daddy was fishing.</font></b>

1477
02:10:56,401 --> 02:10:57,803
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">For salmon.</font></b>

1478
02:10:58,303 --> 02:11:01,607
<b><font face="Arial Narrow">Abel now has disappeared
into the communist world.</font></b>

